@Reasoning:
Signature type variables are shared within ONE signature instantiation -
'a -> 'a list must produce v -> v list, not v1 -> v2 list - and fresh
ACROSS instantiations so every use site of a registry member constrains
its own copy (the same per-use polymorphism instantiate gives
let-generalized bindings). The cursor record memoizes up to four
variables (slots a..d at offsets 16..40) created lazily on first
reference.
@End Reasoning

Process called "sig_cursor_var" takes analyzer as Integer, cursor as Integer, slot as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get or lazily create the signature type variable for a slot

    Let var_offset be 16 plus (slot multiplied by 8)
    Let existing be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cursor, var_offset
    If existing is not equal to 0:
        Return existing
    End If

    Let fresh be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, var_offset, fresh
    Return fresh
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recursive-descent parser over the prefix signature notation documented
at seed_dotnet_module. Prefix notation needs no parentheses or
precedence: every constructor consumes exactly its payload count, so one
character of lookahead (the character itself) drives the whole parse.
The cursor record carries [signature string @0, position @8, variable
slots @16..40]. Registry strings are compiler-internal, but a malformed
character still degrades to TYPE_ERROR (absorbing unification) rather
than reading past the buffer.
@End Reasoning

Process called "parse_sig_type" takes analyzer as Integer, cursor as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse one type from the signature cursor

    Let sig be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cursor, 0
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cursor, 8
    Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with sig, pos
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, 8, pos plus 1

    If ch is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    If ch is equal to 62:  Note: '>' function
        Let param be proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Let ret be proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, param, ret
    End If

    If ch is equal to 108:  Note: 'l' list
        Let inner be proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_LIST, inner
    End If
    If ch is equal to 114:  Note: 'r' array
        Set inner to proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_ARRAY, inner
    End If
    If ch is equal to 113:  Note: 'q' seq
        Set inner to proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_SEQUENCE, inner
    End If
    If ch is equal to 111:  Note: 'o' option
        Set inner to proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_OPTION, inner
    End If
    If ch is equal to 50:  Note: '2' array2d
        Set inner to proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_ARRAY2D, inner
    End If
    If ch is equal to 51:  Note: '3' array3d
        Set inner to proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_ARRAY3D, inner
    End If
    If ch is equal to 69:  Note: 'E' set
        Set inner to proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_SET, inner
    End If

    If ch is equal to 77:  Note: 'M' map
        Let key_type be proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Let value_type be proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_MAP, key_type, value_type
    End If

    If ch is equal to 82:  Note: 'R' Result union
        Let result_cases be proc list_create from List
        proc list_append from List with result_cases, "Ok"
        proc list_append from List with result_cases, "Error"
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_UNION, "Result", result_cases
    End If

    If ch is equal to 116:  Note: 't' tuple
        Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cursor, 8
        Let count_ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with sig, pos
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, 8, pos plus 1
        Let elem_count be count_ch minus 48
        If elem_count is less than 0:
            Return TYPE_ERROR
        End If
        Let elems be proc list_create from List
        Let e be 0
        While e is less than elem_count:
            Let elem be proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
            proc list_append from List with elems, elem
            Set e to e plus 1
        End While
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_TUPLE, elems
    End If

    If ch is equal to 97:  Note: 'a'
        Return proc sig_cursor_var with analyzer, cursor, 0
    End If
    If ch is equal to 98:  Note: 'b'
        Return proc sig_cursor_var with analyzer, cursor, 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 99:  Note: 'c'
        Return proc sig_cursor_var with analyzer, cursor, 2
    End If
    If ch is equal to 100:  Note: 'd'
        Return proc sig_cursor_var with analyzer, cursor, 3
    End If

    If ch is equal to 73:  Note: 'I'
        Return TYPE_INT
    End If
    If ch is equal to 70:  Note: 'F'
        Return TYPE_FLOAT
    End If
    If ch is equal to 83:  Note: 'S'
        Return TYPE_STRING
    End If
    If ch is equal to 66:  Note: 'B'
        Return TYPE_BOOL
    End If
    If ch is equal to 85:  Note: 'U'
        Return TYPE_UNIT
    End If
    If ch is equal to 67:  Note: 'C'
        Return TYPE_CHAR
    End If
    If ch is equal to 79:  Note: 'O'
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If
    If ch is equal to 68:  Note: 'D'
        Return TYPE_DECIMAL
    End If

    Return TYPE_ERROR
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public instantiation entry: builds one fresh copy of a registered
member's type from its signature string. A fresh cursor per call gives
per-use polymorphism directly - the parse allocates new variable records
for a..d every time, so List.map used at two types constrains two
independent copies, exactly like scheme instantiation.
@End Reasoning

Process called "member_signature_type" takes analyzer as Integer, signature as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Instantiate a registry signature string as a fresh type

    If signature is equal to 0:
        Return proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    End If

    Let cursor be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, 48
    If cursor is equal to 0:
        Return proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, 0, signature
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cursor, 40, 0

    Return proc parse_sig_type with analyzer, cursor
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resets analyzer state for a fresh run: empties the diagnostic lists,
drops every substitution and fresh-variable counter, releases all pooled
records (and clears the pool), clears the registries, pops every
lingering local scope, clears the module-level symbol table and module
table, and clears + re-seeds the type environment (its registered type
records were pool-owned, so clearing prevents dangling references after
the pool sweep; built-in codes are integers and re-seed cheaply).
@End Reasoning

Process called "clear_analysis_results" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Clear previous analysis results for a fresh run

    Let error_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 40
    proc list_clear from List with error_list

    Let warning_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    proc list_clear from List with warning_list

    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24

    Let alloc_pool be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 32
    Let pool_count be proc list_length from List with alloc_pool
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than pool_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with alloc_pool, i
        If block is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with block
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_clear from List with alloc_pool

    Let subst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 0
    proc list_clear from List with subst
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with solver, 8, 0

    Let match_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 16
    proc list_clear from List with match_registry

    Let definitions be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 24
    proc list_clear from List with definitions

    Let env_types be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 40
    proc list_clear from List with env_types

    Let scope_stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let scope_count be proc list_length from List with scope_stack
    Let s be 0
    While s is less than scope_count:
        Let scope_table be proc list_get from List with scope_stack, s
        If scope_table is not equal to 0:
            proc hashtable_destroy from Dict with scope_table
        End If
        Set s to s plus 1
    End While
    proc list_clear from List with scope_stack

    Let symbol_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    proc hashtable_clear from Dict with symbol_table

    Let module_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 32
    proc hashtable_clear from Dict with module_table

    Let measure_system be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 56
    proc hashtable_clear from Dict with measure_system

    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
    proc hashtable_clear from Dict with type_env
    proc setup_fsharp_builtins with analyzer

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Representation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Type values are polymorphic: bare primitive codes below 65536 ARE their
own tag; larger values are pointers whose first field is the tag. This
accessor resolves the polymorphism once so every consumer dispatches on
one integer.
@End Reasoning

Process called "type_tag" takes type_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the type tag of a bare code or composite type record

    If type_value is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_UNKNOWN
    End If
    If type_value is less than 65536:
        Return type_value
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_value, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-payload composite constructor (list/array/option/seq/async/
computation element types, tuple element-list carrier, record name
carrier, generic variable id). 16 bytes: tag, payload.
@End Reasoning

Process called "make_type1" takes analyzer as Integer, tag as Integer, payload as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate a pooled [tag, payload] composite type record

    Let record be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, 16
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with record, 0, tag
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with record, 8, payload
    Return record
End Process

@Reasoning:
Two-payload composite constructor (function param/return, measure
base/unit, union name/case-list). 24 bytes: tag, first, second.
@End Reasoning

Process called "make_type2" takes analyzer as Integer, tag as Integer, first as Integer, second as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate a pooled [tag, first, second] composite type record

    Let record be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, 24
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with record, 0, tag
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with record, 8, first
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with record, 16, second
    Return record
End Process

@Reasoning:
Fresh type variables drive the unification engine: every unconstrained
binder starts as a fresh variable that later unification resolves. Ids
index the solver's substitution List directly, so creation appends one
unbound (0) slot and the variable record carries the id.
@End Reasoning

Process called "fresh_type_var" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate a fresh unbound type variable

    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    Let var_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with solver, 8, var_id plus 1

    Let subst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 0
    proc list_append from List with subst, 0

    Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_GENERIC, var_id
End Process

@Reasoning:
Follows the substitution chain from a type variable to its current
binding (or the variable itself when unbound). Every unification and
inspection path resolves first so decisions are made on the most
concrete knowledge available. Iterative (not recursive) so chains of
any length resolve in constant stack.
@End Reasoning

Process called "resolve_type" takes analyzer as Integer, type_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Resolve a type through the substitution store

    Let current be type_value
    Let resolving be 1
    While resolving is equal to 1:
        If current is equal to 0:
            Set resolving to 0
            Continue
        End If
        If current is less than 65536:
            Set resolving to 0
            Continue
        End If

        Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with current, 0
        If tag is not equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
            Set resolving to 0
            Continue
        End If

        Let var_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with current, 8
        Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
        Let subst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 0
        Let bound be proc list_get from List with subst, var_id
        If bound is equal to 0:
            Set resolving to 0
            Continue
        End If

        Set current to bound
    End While

    Return current
End Process

@Reasoning:
The occurs check prevents infinite types: binding 'a to a composite that
contains 'a (e.g. 'a = 'a -> int) would make resolution diverge.
Recursive structural walk over resolved types; returns 1 when the
variable occurs inside the candidate binding.
@End Reasoning

Process called "occurs_check" takes analyzer as Integer, var_id as Integer, type_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether type variable var_id occurs inside type_value

    Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, type_value
    If resolved is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If resolved is less than 65536:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 0

    If tag is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Let other_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        If other_id is equal to var_id:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Let param be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let found be proc occurs_check with analyzer, var_id, param
        If found is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let ret be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 16
        Return proc occurs_check with analyzer, var_id, ret
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_MAP:
        Let key_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Set found to proc occurs_check with analyzer, var_id, key_type
        If found is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let value_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 16
        Return proc occurs_check with analyzer, var_id, value_type
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_TUPLE:
        Let elems be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let count be proc list_length from List with elems
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let elem be proc list_get from List with elems, i
            Set found to proc occurs_check with analyzer, var_id, elem
            If found is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_wrapper be 0
    If tag is equal to TYPE_LIST:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_OPTION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_SEQUENCE:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ASYNC:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_COMPUTATION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_MEASURE:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY2D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY3D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_SET:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If

    If is_wrapper is equal to 1:
        Let inner be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Return proc occurs_check with analyzer, var_id, inner
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
The unification primitive. Resolves both sides, succeeds immediately on
identity, lets TYPE_ERROR and TYPE_ANY absorb anything (error recovery
and obj-typed interop must not cascade), binds free variables (with the
occurs check), and otherwise requires equal tags plus recursive payload
agreement: functions unify componentwise, element wrappers unify their
element, tuples require equal arity plus pairwise unification, records
and unions unify by declared name, measured types unify base and unit.
Returns 1 on success, 0 on mismatch; callers attach diagnostics because
only they know the source construct being checked.
@End Reasoning

Process called "unify_types" takes analyzer as Integer, type1 as Integer, type2 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Unify two types in the substitution store

    Let t1 be proc resolve_type with analyzer, type1
    Let t2 be proc resolve_type with analyzer, type2

    If t1 is equal to t2:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let tag1 be proc type_tag with t1
    Let tag2 be proc type_tag with t2

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ERROR:
        Return 1
    End If
    If tag2 is equal to TYPE_ERROR:
        Return 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ANY:
        Return 1
    End If
    If tag2 is equal to TYPE_ANY:
        Return 1
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Let var_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let cyclic be proc occurs_check with analyzer, var_id, t2
        If cyclic is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
        Let subst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 0
        proc list_set from List with subst, var_id, t2
        Return 1
    End If

    If tag2 is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Set var_id to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Set cyclic to proc occurs_check with analyzer, var_id, t1
        If cyclic is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set solver to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
        Set subst to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 0
        proc list_set from List with subst, var_id, t1
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: F# sequence covariance: list, array, and set values flow into
    Note: seq<'T> positions ('T list :> seq<'T>). Unification call sites
    Note: pass the ACTUAL type first and the EXPECTED type second, so the
    Note: coercion is directional - a seq value does NOT unify into a
    Note: list position, exactly as F# rejects it. Element types unify.
    If tag2 is equal to TYPE_SEQUENCE:
        Let seq_coercible be 0
        If tag1 is equal to TYPE_LIST:
            Set seq_coercible to 1
        End If
        If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ARRAY:
            Set seq_coercible to 1
        End If
        If tag1 is equal to TYPE_SET:
            Set seq_coercible to 1
        End If
        If seq_coercible is equal to 1:
            If t1 is greater than or equal to 65536:
                If t2 is greater than or equal to 65536:
                    Let coerce_inner1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
                    Let coerce_inner2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
                    Return proc unify_types with analyzer, coerce_inner1, coerce_inner2
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If tag1 is not equal to tag2:
        Return 0
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Let param1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let param2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Let ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, param1, param2
        If ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let ret1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 16
        Let ret2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 16
        Return proc unify_types with analyzer, ret1, ret2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_MAP:
        Let key1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let key2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Set ok to proc unify_types with analyzer, key1, key2
        If ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let val1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 16
        Let val2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 16
        Return proc unify_types with analyzer, val1, val2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_TUPLE:
        Let elems1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let elems2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Let count1 be proc list_length from List with elems1
        Let count2 be proc list_length from List with elems2
        If count1 is not equal to count2:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count1:
            Let e1 be proc list_get from List with elems1, i
            Let e2 be proc list_get from List with elems2, i
            Set ok to proc unify_types with analyzer, e1, e2
            If ok is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_wrapper be 0
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_LIST:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ARRAY:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_OPTION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_SEQUENCE:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ASYNC:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_COMPUTATION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ARRAY2D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ARRAY3D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_SET:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If

    If is_wrapper is equal to 1:
        Let inner1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let inner2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Return proc unify_types with analyzer, inner1, inner2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_RECORD:
        Let name1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let name2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        If name1 is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        If name2 is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with name1, name2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_UNION:
        Set name1 to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Set name2 to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with name1, name2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_MEASURE:
        Let base1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let base2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Set ok to proc unify_types with analyzer, base1, base2
        If ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let unit1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 16
        Let unit2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 16
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with unit1, unit2
    End If

    Note: Equal tags with no payload comparison remaining
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Pure compatibility predicate: answers whether two types could describe
the same value WITHOUT mutating the substitution store. Free variables
are compatible with anything (they could still be bound that way);
otherwise the structural rules mirror unify_types. Used by checks that
must not commit speculative bindings (literal-pattern admissibility).
@End Reasoning

Process called "types_compatible" takes analyzer as Integer, type1 as Integer, type2 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Non-mutating structural compatibility test

    Let t1 be proc resolve_type with analyzer, type1
    Let t2 be proc resolve_type with analyzer, type2

    If t1 is equal to t2:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let tag1 be proc type_tag with t1
    Let tag2 be proc type_tag with t2

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ERROR:
        Return 1
    End If
    If tag2 is equal to TYPE_ERROR:
        Return 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ANY:
        Return 1
    End If
    If tag2 is equal to TYPE_ANY:
        Return 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Return 1
    End If
    If tag2 is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: F# sequence covariance mirror of unify_types: a list, array, or
    Note: set value is compatible with a seq<'T> expectation
    If tag2 is equal to TYPE_SEQUENCE:
        Let seq_coercible be 0
        If tag1 is equal to TYPE_LIST:
            Set seq_coercible to 1
        End If
        If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ARRAY:
            Set seq_coercible to 1
        End If
        If tag1 is equal to TYPE_SET:
            Set seq_coercible to 1
        End If
        If seq_coercible is equal to 1:
            If t1 is greater than or equal to 65536:
                If t2 is greater than or equal to 65536:
                    Let coerce_inner1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
                    Let coerce_inner2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
                    Return proc types_compatible with analyzer, coerce_inner1, coerce_inner2
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If tag1 is not equal to tag2:
        Return 0
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Let param1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let param2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Let ok be proc types_compatible with analyzer, param1, param2
        If ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let ret1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 16
        Let ret2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 16
        Return proc types_compatible with analyzer, ret1, ret2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_MAP:
        Let key1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let key2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Set ok to proc types_compatible with analyzer, key1, key2
        If ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let val1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 16
        Let val2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 16
        Return proc types_compatible with analyzer, val1, val2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_TUPLE:
        Let elems1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let elems2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Let count1 be proc list_length from List with elems1
        Let count2 be proc list_length from List with elems2
        If count1 is not equal to count2:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count1:
            Let e1 be proc list_get from List with elems1, i
            Let e2 be proc list_get from List with elems2, i
            Set ok to proc types_compatible with analyzer, e1, e2
            If ok is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_wrapper be 0
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_LIST:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ARRAY:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_OPTION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_SEQUENCE:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ASYNC:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_COMPUTATION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ARRAY2D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_ARRAY3D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_SET:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If

    If is_wrapper is equal to 1:
        Let inner1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let inner2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Return proc types_compatible with analyzer, inner1, inner2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_RECORD:
        Let name1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Let name2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        If name1 is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        If name2 is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with name1, name2
    End If

    If tag1 is equal to TYPE_UNION:
        Set name1 to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t1, 8
        Set name2 to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t2, 8
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with name1, name2
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Predicate testing whether a value is a function type. Accepts both the
bare TYPE_FUNCTION code (degenerate, no payload available) and composite
function records; rejects everything else so application typing fails
fast with a clear diagnostic.
@End Reasoning

Process called "is_function_type" takes type_info as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if a type value is a function type

    Let tag be proc type_tag with type_info
    If tag is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Destructor for the parameter side of a function-type record (T1 -> T2
stores T1 at offset 8). The bare TYPE_FUNCTION code carries no payload
so it degrades to TYPE_ANY rather than dereferencing a non-pointer.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_function_param_type" takes function_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get parameter type from a function type

    If function_type is less than 65536:
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If
    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with function_type, 0
    If tag is not equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with function_type, 8
End Process

@Reasoning:
Destructor for the return side of a function-type record (offset 16),
with the same bare-code degradation as the parameter accessor.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_function_return_type" takes function_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get return type from a function type

    If function_type is less than 65536:
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If
    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with function_type, 0
    If tag is not equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with function_type, 16
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds the curried function type t1 -> t2 -> ... -> result from a List
of parameter types, folding right so the chain associates exactly as F#
applications consume it one argument at a time. An empty parameter list
yields unit -> result (the F# thunk shape).
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_function_type" takes analyzer as Integer, param_types as Integer, return_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create curried function type from parameter list and return type

    Let count be proc list_length from List with param_types
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, TYPE_UNIT, return_type
    End If

    Let result be return_type
    Let i be count minus 1
    While i is greater than or equal to 0:
        Let param be proc list_get from List with param_types, i
        Set result to proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, param, result
        Set i to i minus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
One step of application typing: applies a function type to one argument
type and yields the result type. Free-variable callees are bound to a
fresh param -> fresh return shape first (this is how inference learns a
lambda parameter is itself a function), TYPE_ANY callees absorb the
application (cross-module values), genuine function records unify the
argument against the parameter, and everything else is the classic
"not a function" error.
@End Reasoning

Process called "apply_function_type" takes analyzer as Integer, function_type as Integer, argument_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Apply a function type to one argument type

    Let fn be proc resolve_type with analyzer, function_type
    Let tag be proc type_tag with fn

    If tag is equal to TYPE_ERROR:
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ANY:
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Let fresh_param be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Let fresh_ret be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Let fn_shape be proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, fresh_param, fresh_ret
        Let bound be proc unify_types with analyzer, fn, fn_shape
        If bound is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Expression is not a function"
            Return TYPE_ERROR
        End If
        Let arg_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, argument_type, fresh_param
        If arg_ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Argument type mismatch"
            Return TYPE_ERROR
        End If
        Return fresh_ret
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Let param be proc get_function_param_type with fn
        Set arg_ok to proc unify_types with analyzer, argument_type, param
        If arg_ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Argument type mismatch"
            Return TYPE_ERROR
        End If
        Return proc get_function_return_type with fn
    End If

    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Expression is not a function"
    Return TYPE_ERROR
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Let-Polymorphism: Generalization and Instantiation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Membership test over an integer id List; the free-variable collectors
need set semantics and the lists involved are small (a binding rarely
has more than a handful of free variables), so a linear scan is the
right structure.
@End Reasoning

Process called "type_var_list_contains" takes id_list as Integer, var_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether a type-variable id List contains the given id

    If id_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc list_length from List with id_list
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let entry be proc list_get from List with id_list, i
        If entry is equal to var_id:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Collects the ids of every UNBOUND type variable reachable from a type
into the accumulator list (deduplicated). Resolution happens at each
step so variables already solved by unification contribute their
binding's free variables, not themselves. The walk mirrors occurs_check
structurally: functions and measures recurse into both payloads, tuples
into every element, single-payload wrappers into their element; records,
unions, and primitive codes carry no type variables.
@End Reasoning

Process called "collect_free_type_vars" takes analyzer as Integer, type_value as Integer, acc as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Accumulate the unbound type-variable ids reachable from a type

    Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, type_value
    If resolved is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If resolved is less than 65536:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 0

    If tag is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Let var_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let already be proc type_var_list_contains with acc, var_id
        If already is equal to 0:
            proc list_append from List with acc, var_id
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Let param be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, param, acc
        Let ret be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 16
        proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, ret, acc
        Return 1
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_MAP:
        Let key_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, key_type, acc
        Let value_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 16
        proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, value_type, acc
        Return 1
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_MEASURE:
        Let base be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, base, acc
        Return 1
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_TUPLE:
        Let elems be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let count be proc list_length from List with elems
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let elem be proc list_get from List with elems, i
            proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, elem, acc
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_wrapper be 0
    If tag is equal to TYPE_LIST:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_OPTION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_SEQUENCE:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ASYNC:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_COMPUTATION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY2D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY3D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_SET:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If

    If is_wrapper is equal to 1:
        Let inner be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, inner, acc
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Hindley-Milner generalization at a let binding: quantify exactly the
type variables free in the binding's type but NOT free in the
environment. The environment surface is the solver's env-types list;
env_limit caps the scan so recursive bindings exclude their own
pre-bound self entry (which would otherwise anchor every variable of
the binding and block generalization). The result is a pooled
[count, id, id, ...] quantifier record, or 0 when nothing generalizes -
the monomorphic case, which instantiation treats as a plain type. The
temporary id Lists are destroyed before returning; the quantifier
record is pool-owned so the analyzer's sweep frees it.
@End Reasoning

Process called "generalize" takes analyzer as Integer, type_value as Integer, env_limit as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build the quantifier record for a let-bound type (0 if monomorphic)

    Let type_vars be proc list_create from List
    proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, type_value, type_vars

    Let type_var_count be proc list_length from List with type_vars
    If type_var_count is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with type_vars
        Return 0
    End If

    Let env_vars be proc list_create from List
    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    Let env_types be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 40
    Let env_count be proc list_length from List with env_types
    Let scan_limit be env_limit
    If scan_limit is greater than env_count:
        Set scan_limit to env_count
    End If

    Let e be 0
    While e is less than scan_limit:
        Let env_entry be proc list_get from List with env_types, e
        Let env_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with env_entry, 8
        proc collect_free_type_vars with analyzer, env_type, env_vars
        Set e to e plus 1
    End While

    Let quantified be proc list_create from List
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than type_var_count:
        Let var_id be proc list_get from List with type_vars, i
        Let in_env be proc type_var_list_contains with env_vars, var_id
        If in_env is equal to 0:
            proc list_append from List with quantified, var_id
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let quant_count be proc list_length from List with quantified
    If quant_count is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with type_vars
        proc list_destroy from List with env_vars
        proc list_destroy from List with quantified
        Return 0
    End If

    Let scheme be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, 8 plus (quant_count multiplied by 8)
    If scheme is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with type_vars
        proc list_destroy from List with env_vars
        proc list_destroy from List with quantified
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with scheme, 0, quant_count
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than quant_count:
        Set var_id to proc list_get from List with quantified, i
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with scheme, 8 plus (i multiplied by 8), var_id
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc list_destroy from List with type_vars
    proc list_destroy from List with env_vars
    proc list_destroy from List with quantified
    Return scheme
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recursive copy step of instantiation: rebuilds the type with every
quantified variable replaced by its pre-allocated fresh counterpart
(fresh_list is positionally parallel to the scheme's id array so the
SAME quantified variable maps to the SAME fresh variable everywhere it
occurs - 'a -> 'a must instantiate to v -> v, not v1 -> v2).
Non-quantified variables and variable-free types are returned as-is:
sharing them is sound because instantiation never mutates, and it keeps
allocation proportional to the polymorphic part of the type.
@End Reasoning

Process called "instantiate_type" takes analyzer as Integer, type_value as Integer, scheme as Integer, fresh_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Copy a type replacing quantified variables with fresh ones

    Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, type_value
    If resolved is equal to 0:
        Return resolved
    End If
    If resolved is less than 65536:
        Return resolved
    End If

    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 0

    If tag is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Let var_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let quant_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scheme, 0
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than quant_count:
            Let quant_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scheme, 8 plus (i multiplied by 8)
            If quant_id is equal to var_id:
                Return proc list_get from List with fresh_list, i
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return resolved
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Let param be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let ret be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 16
        Let new_param be proc instantiate_type with analyzer, param, scheme, fresh_list
        Let new_ret be proc instantiate_type with analyzer, ret, scheme, fresh_list
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, new_param, new_ret
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_MAP:
        Let key_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let value_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 16
        Let new_key be proc instantiate_type with analyzer, key_type, scheme, fresh_list
        Let new_value be proc instantiate_type with analyzer, value_type, scheme, fresh_list
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_MAP, new_key, new_value
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_MEASURE:
        Let base be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let unit be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 16
        Let new_base be proc instantiate_type with analyzer, base, scheme, fresh_list
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_MEASURE, new_base, unit
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_TUPLE:
        Let elems be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let count be proc list_length from List with elems
        Let new_elems be proc list_create from List
        Set i to 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let elem be proc list_get from List with elems, i
            Let new_elem be proc instantiate_type with analyzer, elem, scheme, fresh_list
            proc list_append from List with new_elems, new_elem
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_TUPLE, new_elems
    End If

    Let is_wrapper be 0
    If tag is equal to TYPE_LIST:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_OPTION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_SEQUENCE:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ASYNC:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_COMPUTATION:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY2D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY3D:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_SET:
        Set is_wrapper to 1
    End If

    If is_wrapper is equal to 1:
        Let inner be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let new_inner be proc instantiate_type with analyzer, inner, scheme, fresh_list
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, tag, new_inner
    End If

    Return resolved
End Process

@Reasoning:
Hindley-Milner instantiation at a use site: a polymorphic binding's type
is copied with one fresh variable per quantified variable, so every use
constrains its own copy - let id = fun x -> x then typechecks at int and
at bool in the same scope. Monomorphic bindings (scheme 0) return the
stored type unchanged, preserving exactly the pre-polymorphism
behaviour (and the value restriction: non-generalized bindings share
one type across uses).
@End Reasoning

Process called "instantiate" takes analyzer as Integer, type_value as Integer, scheme as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Instantiate a generalized type with fresh variables per use

    If scheme is equal to 0:
        Return type_value
    End If

    Let quant_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scheme, 0
    If quant_count is equal to 0:
        Return type_value
    End If

    Let fresh_list be proc list_create from List
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than quant_count:
        Let fresh be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        proc list_append from List with fresh_list, fresh
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let result be proc instantiate_type with analyzer, type_value, scheme, fresh_list
    proc list_destroy from List with fresh_list
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Scopes, Symbols, and Diagnostics
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Opens a new local scope frame: a fresh hashtable pushed onto
scope_stack. Used at lambda entry, let-expression bodies, match arms,
for-loop bodies, and computation/async bodies. The module-level
symbol_table stays beneath the stack so locals shadow module bindings
exactly as F# scoping requires.
@End Reasoning

Process called "push_scope" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Push new local scope onto scope stack

    Let scope_stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let new_scope be proc hashtable_create from Dict
    proc list_append from List with scope_stack, new_scope

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Restores the previous scope after a nested binding region completes:
pops and destroys the top hashtable (its symbol records remain pool-
owned for the unused-binding sweep). Pairing push/pop is the caller's
invariant.
@End Reasoning

Process called "pop_scope" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Pop current local scope from scope stack

    Let scope_stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let scope_count be proc list_length from List with scope_stack

    If scope_count is greater than 0:
        Let top_index be scope_count minus 1
        Let scope_to_remove be proc list_get from List with scope_stack, top_index
        proc list_remove from List with scope_stack, top_index
        proc hashtable_destroy from Dict with scope_to_remove

        Note: Drop env-type entries recorded at the departing depth so
        Note: generalization no longer treats the popped bindings' type
        Note: variables as environment-bound. Entries are pool-owned, so
        Note: truncation here is bookkeeping only - the pool frees them.
        Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
        Let env_types be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 40
        Let trimming be 1
        While trimming is equal to 1:
            Let env_count be proc list_length from List with env_types
            If env_count is equal to 0:
                Set trimming to 0
                Continue
            End If
            Let last_entry be proc list_get from List with env_types, env_count minus 1
            Let entry_depth be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with last_entry, 0
            If entry_depth is less than scope_count:
                Set trimming to 0
                Continue
            End If
            proc list_remove from List with env_types, env_count minus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
The innermost binding surface: the top of scope_stack when local scopes
are open, otherwise the module-level symbol_table. Every definition
lands here so shadowing falls out of lookup order.
@End Reasoning

Process called "current_scope_table" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the innermost scope's hashtable

    Let scope_stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let scope_count be proc list_length from List with scope_stack
    If scope_count is greater than 0:
        Let top_index be scope_count minus 1
        Return proc list_get from List with scope_stack, top_index
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Creates a symbol record (type, is_used, name, is_local, scheme) and
binds it in the innermost scope. Local definitions (any open scope) also
register in the definitions list for the unused-binding sweep;
module-level definitions are exported surface and are exempt from unused
analysis, matching the F# compiler's default warning behaviour. Every
definition additionally records a [depth, type] pair in the solver's
env-types list - the environment surface generalization scans - which
pop_scope truncates when the binding goes out of scope. The scheme slot
starts monomorphic (0); analyze_let_binding_declaration writes the
quantifier record for generalizable let bindings.
@End Reasoning

Process called "define_symbol" takes analyzer as Integer, symbol_name as Integer, symbol_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Bind a name to a type in the innermost scope

    If symbol_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let symbol be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, 40
    If symbol is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let scope_stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let scope_count be proc list_length from List with scope_stack
    Let is_local be 0
    If scope_count is greater than 0:
        Set is_local to 1
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with symbol, 0, symbol_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with symbol, 8, 0   Note: is_used
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with symbol, 16, symbol_name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with symbol, 24, is_local
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with symbol, 32, 0  Note: scheme quantifiers

    Let scope_table be proc current_scope_table with analyzer
    proc hashtable_set from Dict with scope_table, symbol_name, symbol

    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    Let definitions be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 24
    proc list_append from List with definitions, symbol

    Let env_entry be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, 16
    If env_entry is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with env_entry, 0, scope_count
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with env_entry, 8, symbol_type
        Let env_types be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 40
        proc list_append from List with env_types, env_entry
    End If

    Return symbol
End Process

@Reasoning:
Walks the scope chain from innermost to outermost, then the module-level
symbol_table, so shadowed names resolve to their innermost binder. Hits
mark the symbol used (feeding the unused-binding sweep). Returns the
symbol record or 0 when unbound.
@End Reasoning

Process called "lookup_symbol" takes analyzer as Integer, symbol_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Look up a symbol through the scope chain

    If symbol_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let scope_stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let scope_count be proc list_length from List with scope_stack
    Let scope_index be scope_count minus 1

    While scope_index is greater than or equal to 0:
        Let scope_table be proc list_get from List with scope_stack, scope_index
        Let scope_symbol be proc hashtable_get from Dict with scope_table, symbol_name
        If scope_symbol is not equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with scope_symbol, 8, 1
            Return scope_symbol
        End If
        Set scope_index to scope_index minus 1
    End While

    Let symbol_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    Let module_symbol be proc hashtable_get from Dict with symbol_table, symbol_name
    If module_symbol is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with module_symbol, 8, 1
        Return module_symbol
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Accessor hiding the symbol record layout (type lives at offset 0) from
the inference paths.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_symbol_type" takes symbol_info as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the bound type from a symbol record

    If symbol_info is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with symbol_info, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Adds a pattern-introduced binding (the x in Some x) to the current
scope with the supplied type. Shadowing rules apply automatically via
define_symbol's innermost-scope binding.
@End Reasoning

Process called "add_pattern_variable" takes analyzer as Integer, var_name as Integer, var_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Bind a pattern variable in the current scope

    Let symbol be proc define_symbol with analyzer, var_name, var_type
    If symbol is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends a fatal diagnostic to the error_list (offset 40).
has_semantic_errors returning nonzero means the driver must not proceed
to code generation. Message strings are either static literals or
pooled concatenations, both alive for the analyzer's lifetime.
@End Reasoning

Process called "add_semantic_error" takes analyzer as Integer, error_message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add semantic error to error list

    Let error_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 40
    proc list_append from List with error_list, error_message

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Companion for non-fatal diagnostics (incomplete match, redundant arm,
unused binding). The driver may proceed to code generation when only
warnings exist.
@End Reasoning

Process called "add_semantic_warning" takes analyzer as Integer, warning_message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add semantic warning to warning list

    Let warning_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    proc list_append from List with warning_list, warning_message

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Names, Type Expressions, and Declaration Registration
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Resolves a type name through the type environment (built-ins plus
registered declarations). Names this single-module analysis cannot see -
dotted .NET paths and types supplied by opened assemblies - resolve to
TYPE_ANY because rejecting them would produce false errors on every
interop program; TYPE_ANY then absorbs unification exactly like obj.
Type variables ('a spellings, apostrophe lead byte) resolve to a fresh
unification variable.
@End Reasoning

Process called "resolve_type_name" takes analyzer as Integer, type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Resolve a type name to a type value

    If type_name is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If

    Let first_char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with type_name, 0
    If first_char is equal to 39:  Note: apostrophe - 'a type variable
        Return proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    End If

    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
    Let known be proc hashtable_get from Dict with type_env, type_name
    If known is not equal to 0:
        Return known
    End If

    Return TYPE_ANY
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a parsed type expression (AST_TYPE_NAME, AST_TYPE_FUNCTION,
AST_TYPE_APPLICATION) to a type value. Generic applications map the
well-known unary constructors (option/list/array/seq/Async and their
prefix spellings Option/List/Array/Seq) to their dedicated composite
shapes so inference reasons structurally about them; other constructor
names resolve through the environment (registered abbreviations) or
degrade to TYPE_ANY for cross-module generics.
@End Reasoning

Process called "resolve_type_expr" takes analyzer as Integer, type_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Resolve a type-expression AST node to a type value

    If type_node is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 0

    If node_kind is equal to AST_TYPE_NAME from Parser:
        Let name_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 8
        Let type_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with name_token
        Return proc resolve_type_name with analyzer, type_name
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to AST_TYPE_FUNCTION from Parser:
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 16
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 24
        If child_count is less than 2:
            Return TYPE_ANY
        End If
        Let arg_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
        Let result_node be proc list_get from List with children, 1
        Let arg_type be proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, arg_node
        Let result_type be proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, result_node
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, arg_type, result_type
    End If

    Note: Tuple types (int * string) carry their element list in the same
    Note: [TYPE_TUPLE, element List] shape infer_tuple_type builds, so
    Note: annotated tuples unify structurally with inferred tuple values
    If node_kind is equal to AST_TYPE_TUPLE from Parser:
        Set children to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 16
        Set child_count to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 24

        Let element_types be proc list_create from List
        Let t be 0
        While t is less than child_count:
            Let element_node be proc list_get from List with children, t
            Let element_type be proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, element_node
            proc list_append from List with element_types, element_type
            Set t to t plus 1
        End While

        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_TUPLE, element_types
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to AST_TYPE_APPLICATION from Parser:
        Set name_token to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 8
        Let ctor_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with name_token
        Set children to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 16
        Set child_count to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_node, 24

        Let first_arg be TYPE_ANY
        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let first_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
            Set first_arg to proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, first_node
        End If

        Let is_option be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "option"
        If is_option is equal to 0:
            Set is_option to proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Option"
        End If
        If is_option is equal to 1:
            Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_OPTION, first_arg
        End If

        Let is_list be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "list"
        If is_list is equal to 0:
            Set is_list to proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "List"
        End If
        If is_list is equal to 1:
            Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_LIST, first_arg
        End If

        Let is_array be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "array"
        If is_array is equal to 0:
            Set is_array to proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Array"
        End If
        If is_array is equal to 1:
            Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_ARRAY, first_arg
        End If

        Let is_seq be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "seq"
        If is_seq is equal to 0:
            Set is_seq to proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Seq"
        End If
        If is_seq is equal to 1:
            Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_SEQUENCE, first_arg
        End If

        Let is_async be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Async"
        If is_async is equal to 1:
            Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_ASYNC, first_arg
        End If

        Note: Other constructors: registered abbreviation or cross-module generic
        Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
        Let known be proc hashtable_get from Dict with type_env, ctor_name
        If known is not equal to 0:
            Return known
        End If
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If

    Return TYPE_ANY
End Process

@Reasoning:
Constructor descriptors live in the type environment under a "ctor:"
prefixed key so constructor and type namespaces cannot collide. The
24-byte descriptor carries the owning union type, the payload type, and
the has-payload flag - everything per-use checking needs.
@End Reasoning

Process called "register_constructor" takes analyzer as Integer, ctor_name as Integer, union_type as Integer, payload_type as Integer, has_payload as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Register a discriminated-union constructor descriptor

    Let key be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "ctor:", ctor_name

    Let info be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, 24
    If info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info, 0, union_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info, 8, payload_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info, 16, has_payload

    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
    proc hashtable_set from Dict with type_env, key, info

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Companion lookup over the "ctor:" namespace. The lookup key is pooled by
pool_concat (the hashtable does not copy keys, but lookups don't store
them either, and pooling keeps the key string alive until the analyzer
dies, which is provably safe).
@End Reasoning

Process called "lookup_constructor" takes analyzer as Integer, ctor_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Look up a registered constructor descriptor

    If ctor_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let key be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "ctor:", ctor_name
    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
    Return proc hashtable_get from Dict with type_env, key
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers one type declaration into the environment during the structure
pass so the declarations pass and every later inference resolve forward
references. Record and class/interface declarations register a named
record type (nominal identity); union declarations build the
[TYPE_UNION, name, case-name list] record and register every case
constructor with its resolved payload type; abbreviations register the
resolved aliased type directly so uses see through the alias.
@End Reasoning

Process called "register_type_declaration" takes analyzer as Integer, decl_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Register a type declaration into the type environment

    Let name_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with decl_node, 8
    Let type_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with name_token
    If type_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with decl_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with decl_node, 24
    If child_count is equal to 0:
        proc hashtable_set from Dict with type_env, type_name, TYPE_ANY
        Return 1
    End If

    Let body be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    Let body_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body, 0

    If body_kind is equal to AST_RECORD_TYPE from Parser:
        Let record_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_RECORD, type_name
        proc hashtable_set from Dict with type_env, type_name, record_type
        Return 1
    End If

    If body_kind is equal to AST_UNION_TYPE from Parser:
        Let case_list be proc list_create from List
        Let union_type be proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_UNION, type_name, case_list

        Let case_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body, 16
        Let case_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body, 24
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than case_count:
            Let case_node be proc list_get from List with case_children, i
            Let case_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case_node, 8
            Let case_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with case_token
            If case_name is not equal to 0:
                proc list_append from List with case_list, case_name

                Let payload_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case_node, 16
                Let payload_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case_node, 24
                Let payload_type be 0
                Let has_payload be 0
                If payload_count is greater than 0:
                    Let payload_node be proc list_get from List with payload_children, 0
                    Set payload_type to proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, payload_node
                    Set has_payload to 1
                End If

                proc register_constructor with analyzer, case_name, union_type, payload_type, has_payload
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        proc hashtable_set from Dict with type_env, type_name, union_type
        Return 1
    End If

    If body_kind is equal to AST_CLASS_TYPE from Parser:
        Let class_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_RECORD, type_name
        proc hashtable_set from Dict with type_env, type_name, class_type
        Return 1
    End If

    If body_kind is equal to AST_INTERFACE_TYPE from Parser:
        Let interface_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_RECORD, type_name
        proc hashtable_set from Dict with type_env, type_name, interface_type
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Abbreviation: the body is a type expression
    Let aliased be proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, body
    proc hashtable_set from Dict with type_env, type_name, aliased
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Literal and Operator Typing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Maps a literal token's lexical class to its F# type. Integer-family
tokens (int, bigint) are TYPE_INT, byte literals TYPE_BYTE, float
literals TYPE_FLOAT, decimal literals TYPE_DECIMAL, every string form
(regular, verbatim, triple-quoted, byte, interpolation segments)
TYPE_STRING, chars TYPE_CHAR, true/false TYPE_BOOL, unit TYPE_UNIT, and
null TYPE_ANY (null inhabits reference types; obj-compatibility is the
sound single-module reading).
@End Reasoning

Process called "literal_token_type" takes literal_token as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Map a literal token to its type

    Let token_kind be proc get_token_type from Lexer with literal_token

    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_INT
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_BIGINT from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_INT
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_BYTE from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_BYTE
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_FLOAT from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_FLOAT
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_DECIMAL from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_DECIMAL
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_STRING from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_STRING
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_VERBATIM_STRING from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_STRING
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_TRIPLE_QUOTE_STRING from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_STRING
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_BYTE_STRING from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_STRING
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_INTERP_STRING_START from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_STRING
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_INTERP_STRING_MID from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_STRING
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_CHAR from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_CHAR
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_TRUE from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_BOOL
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_FALSE from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_BOOL
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_UNIT from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_UNIT
    End If
    If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_NULL from Lexer:
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If

    Return TYPE_UNKNOWN
End Process

@Reasoning:
The parser represents infix operators as identifier callees, so operator
typing happens at identifier inference. Each call site receives a FRESH
instantiation (new type variables) because F# operators are polymorphic
per use: arithmetic and comparison operators are 'a -> 'a -> 'a and
'a -> 'a -> bool respectively (statically-resolved member constraints
collapse to same-type constraints in this model, which is exactly the
constraint F# enforces on the default operator set), logical operators
are bool-only, cons builds lists, range builds integer sequences, not
negates bool, and ! dereferences a ref cell (modeled 'a -> 'b because
the ref-cell type itself is opaque here). Returns 0 for non-operator
spellings so identifier lookup proceeds.
@End Reasoning

Process called "operator_function_type" takes analyzer as Integer, op_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build the per-use type of a built-in operator, or 0

    If op_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_arith be proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "+"
    If is_arith is equal to 0:
        Set is_arith to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "-"
    End If
    If is_arith is equal to 0:
        Set is_arith to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "*"
    End If
    If is_arith is equal to 0:
        Set is_arith to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "/"
    End If
    If is_arith is equal to 0:
        Set is_arith to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "%"
    End If
    If is_arith is equal to 0:
        Set is_arith to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "**"
    End If
    If is_arith is equal to 1:
        Let operand be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Let inner be proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, operand, operand
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, operand, inner
    End If

    Let is_compare be proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "="
    If is_compare is equal to 0:
        Set is_compare to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "<>"
    End If
    If is_compare is equal to 0:
        Set is_compare to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "<"
    End If
    If is_compare is equal to 0:
        Set is_compare to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, ">"
    End If
    If is_compare is equal to 0:
        Set is_compare to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "<="
    End If
    If is_compare is equal to 0:
        Set is_compare to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, ">="
    End If
    If is_compare is equal to 1:
        Set operand to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Set inner to proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, operand, TYPE_BOOL
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, operand, inner
    End If

    Let is_logical be proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "&&"
    If is_logical is equal to 0:
        Set is_logical to proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "||"
    End If
    If is_logical is equal to 1:
        Set inner to proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, TYPE_BOOL, TYPE_BOOL
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, TYPE_BOOL, inner
    End If

    Let is_not be proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "not"
    If is_not is equal to 1:
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, TYPE_BOOL, TYPE_BOOL
    End If

    Let is_cons be proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "::"
    If is_cons is equal to 1:
        Set operand to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Let list_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_LIST, operand
        Set inner to proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, list_type, list_type
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, operand, inner
    End If

    Let is_range be proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, ".."
    If is_range is equal to 1:
        Let seq_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_SEQUENCE, TYPE_INT
        Set inner to proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, TYPE_INT, seq_type
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, TYPE_INT, inner
    End If

    Let is_deref be proc string_equals from StringCore with op_name, "!"
    If is_deref is equal to 1:
        Let cell be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Let content be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, cell, content
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds the per-use type of the built-in polymorphic constructors used as
values: Some is 'a -> 'a option, None is 'a option, Ok and Error build a
fresh Result-named union (per-use freshness gives the polymorphism;
same-named unions unify so Ok and Error meet in one match). Returns 0
for other names so the caller proceeds to declared-constructor and
symbol lookup.
@End Reasoning

Process called "builtin_constructor_type" takes analyzer as Integer, ctor_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build the per-use type of a built-in constructor, or 0

    Let is_some be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Some"
    If is_some is equal to 1:
        Let elem be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Let option_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_OPTION, elem
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, elem, option_type
    End If

    Let is_none be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "None"
    If is_none is equal to 1:
        Set elem to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_OPTION, elem
    End If

    Let is_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Ok"
    Let is_err be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Error"
    If is_ok is equal to 1:
        Let result_cases be proc list_create from List
        proc list_append from List with result_cases, "Ok"
        proc list_append from List with result_cases, "Error"
        Let result_union be proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_UNION, "Result", result_cases
        Set elem to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, elem, result_union
    End If
    If is_err is equal to 1:
        Set result_cases to proc list_create from List
        proc list_append from List with result_cases, "Ok"
        proc list_append from List with result_cases, "Error"
        Set result_union to proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_UNION, "Result", result_cases
        Set elem to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, elem, result_union
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expression Type Inference
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Builds the per-use type of the top-level printf family. Their real
FSharp.Core types are PrintfFormat-driven (the format string's
specifiers determine the remaining curried parameters), which a
value-level signature cannot fix statically; the faithful model is
format-string -> fresh, where the fresh result absorbs exactly as many
further applications as the format demands (and infer_application_type
validates the format string's specifier table separately). fprintf and
fprintfn take the writer first. Returns 0 for non-family names so
identifier lookup proceeds.
@End Reasoning

Process called "printf_family_type" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build the per-use type of a printf-family function, or 0

    Let format_index be proc printf_family_format_index with name
    If format_index is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let rest be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    Let fmt_fn be proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, TYPE_STRING, rest
    If format_index is equal to 2:
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, TYPE_ANY, fmt_fn
    End If
    Return fmt_fn
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single classification point for the printf family shared by identifier
typing and format-string checking: the returned index is the position of
the format-string argument in the parser's flattened application shape
(child 0 is the callee), so printf/printfn/sprintf/eprintf/eprintfn/
failwithf format at child 1 and the writer-first fprintf/fprintfn at
child 2. 0 means not a printf-family name.
@End Reasoning

Process called "printf_family_format_index" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Argument index of the format string for printf-family callees

    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_fmt1 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "printf"
    If is_fmt1 is equal to 0:
        Set is_fmt1 to proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "printfn"
    End If
    If is_fmt1 is equal to 0:
        Set is_fmt1 to proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "sprintf"
    End If
    If is_fmt1 is equal to 0:
        Set is_fmt1 to proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "eprintf"
    End If
    If is_fmt1 is equal to 0:
        Set is_fmt1 to proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "eprintfn"
    End If
    If is_fmt1 is equal to 0:
        Set is_fmt1 to proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "failwithf"
    End If
    If is_fmt1 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_fmt2 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "fprintf"
    If is_fmt2 is equal to 0:
        Set is_fmt2 to proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "fprintfn"
    End If
    If is_fmt2 is equal to 1:
        Return 2
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a bare identifier in priority order: built-in operator
spellings (the parser routes infix operators here as identifier
callees), built-in polymorphic constructors, declared union constructors
(payload constructors type as payload -> union, nullary ones as the
union itself), the scope chain (let-generalized bindings instantiate a
fresh copy of their scheme per use, so polymorphic functions check at
every type they are applied at), the printf family, the standard
exception constructors, and finally dotted paths. Dotted resolution
partitions three ways: a qualifier that is a bound value or a
user-declared module is a member access this structural analysis types
fresh; a path whose leading segment is in the .NET core-module registry
(List, Array, Seq, Option, Result, String, Map, Set, Array2D, Array3D
and the nested Array.Parallel / List.Parallel surfaces) resolves through
the nested module tables - the member key is the full dotted spelling,
so depth >2 paths land on their registered nested-module member directly
- and validates membership against the COMPLETE registered surface:
unknown members of known modules are hard errors exactly as F# reports
FS0039, and known members instantiate their REAL registered signature
via member_signature_type, so wrong-shape arguments and over-application
both surface as type errors; any other qualifier (System.*, external
assemblies) is outside this compilation unit's knowledge and degrades to
a documented warning plus a fresh variable. Only a plain undotted name
that nothing resolves is a genuine "Undefined variable" error - the same
partition the F# checker applies given one file.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_identifier_type" takes analyzer as Integer, identifier_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of an identifier reference

    Let name_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with identifier_node, 8
    Let identifier_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with name_token
    If identifier_name is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let op_type be proc operator_function_type with analyzer, identifier_name
    If op_type is not equal to 0:
        Return op_type
    End If

    Let builtin_ctor be proc builtin_constructor_type with analyzer, identifier_name
    If builtin_ctor is not equal to 0:
        Return builtin_ctor
    End If

    Let ctor_info be proc lookup_constructor with analyzer, identifier_name
    If ctor_info is not equal to 0:
        Let union_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ctor_info, 0
        Let has_payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ctor_info, 16
        If has_payload is equal to 1:
            Let payload_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ctor_info, 8
            Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, payload_type, union_type
        End If
        Return union_type
    End If

    Let symbol_info be proc lookup_symbol with analyzer, identifier_name
    If symbol_info is not equal to 0:
        Let symbol_type be proc get_symbol_type with symbol_info
        Let scheme be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with symbol_info, 32
        If scheme is not equal to 0:
            Return proc instantiate with analyzer, symbol_type, scheme
        End If
        Return symbol_type
    End If

    Note: Top-level printf family (printf, printfn, sprintf, ...)
    Let printf_type be proc printf_family_type with analyzer, identifier_name
    If printf_type is not equal to 0:
        Return printf_type
    End If

    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16

    Note: Standard exception constructors (raise (ArgumentException "..."))
    Let exn_key be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "netexn:", identifier_name
    Let exn_known be proc hashtable_get from Dict with type_env, exn_key
    If exn_known is not equal to 0:
        Let exn_arg be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_FUNCTION, exn_arg, TYPE_ANY
    End If

    Let is_dotted be proc string_contains from StringUtils with identifier_name, "."
    If is_dotted is equal to 1:
        Note: Split at the first dot to find the qualifier
        Let name_len be proc string_length from StringCore with identifier_name
        Let dot_pos be 0
        Let scanning be 1
        While scanning is equal to 1:
            If dot_pos is greater than or equal to name_len:
                Set scanning to 0
                Continue
            End If
            Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with identifier_name, dot_pos
            If ch is equal to 46:  Note: '.'
                Set scanning to 0
                Continue
            End If
            Set dot_pos to dot_pos plus 1
        End While

        Let qualifier be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, dot_pos plus 1
        If qualifier is equal to 0:
            Return proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        End If
        Let c be 0
        While c is less than dot_pos:
            Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with identifier_name, c
            proc memory_set_byte from Layout with qualifier, c, ch
            Set c to c plus 1
        End While
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with qualifier, dot_pos, 0

        Note: Member access on a bound value (record.field, instance.Method)
        Let qualifier_symbol be proc lookup_symbol with analyzer, qualifier
        If qualifier_symbol is not equal to 0:
            Return proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        End If

        Note: Qualified reference into a user-declared module or namespace
        Let module_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 32
        Let user_module be proc hashtable_get from Dict with module_table, qualifier
        If user_module is not equal to 0:
            Return proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        End If

        Note: F# core-module registry: complete surface, so membership
        Note: decides. Nested module tables register under their full dotted
        Note: name (netmod:Array.Parallel), so member resolution keys on the
        Note: FULL path: depth >2 spellings (List.Parallel.map) land on their
        Note: nested-module member entry directly, and an unknown member
        Note: under ANY registered module prefix is the FS0039 hard error.
        Let module_key be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "netmod:", qualifier
        Let module_known be proc hashtable_get from Dict with type_env, module_key
        If module_known is not equal to 0:
            Let member_key be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "net:", identifier_name
            Let member_entry be proc hashtable_get from Dict with type_env, member_key
            If member_entry is equal to 0:
                Let unknown_message be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Unknown member: ", identifier_name
                proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, unknown_message
                Return TYPE_ERROR
            End If

            Note: Stored value is the member's real signature string;
            Note: instantiate a fresh copy for this use site
            Return proc member_signature_type with analyzer, member_entry
        End If

        Note: Unknown external qualifier: outside this compilation unit's
        Note: knowledge - warn (documented permissive interop) and proceed
        Let warn_message be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Unresolved external module reference: ", identifier_name
        proc add_semantic_warning with analyzer, warn_message
        Return proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    End If

    Let message be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Undefined variable: ", identifier_name
    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, message
    Return TYPE_ERROR
End Process

@Reasoning:
Application typing over the parser's flattened call shape: child 0 is
the callee (an operator identifier for infix uses), children 1..n are
the arguments in order. Each argument applies one currying step through
apply_function_type, which also teaches free-variable callees their
function shape - so higher-order lambda parameters get usable types from
their first application. printf-family callees additionally validate
their literal format-string argument against the F# specifier
combination table - the same static check the F# compiler runs when a
string literal is adopted as a PrintfFormat.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_application_type" takes analyzer as Integer, app_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a function application

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with app_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with app_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 2:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Function application requires a callee and an argument"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let function_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0

    Note: printf-family format-string validation on the literal argument
    Let function_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with function_node, 0
    If function_kind is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
        Let callee_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with function_node, 8
        Let callee_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with callee_token
        Let fmt_index be proc printf_family_format_index with callee_name
        If fmt_index is greater than 0:
            If child_count is greater than fmt_index:
                Let fmt_node be proc list_get from List with children, fmt_index
                Let fmt_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with fmt_node, 0
                If fmt_kind is equal to AST_LITERAL from Parser:
                    Let fmt_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with fmt_node, 8
                    Let fmt_token_kind be proc get_token_type from Lexer with fmt_token
                    Let is_format_literal be 0
                    If fmt_token_kind is equal to TOKEN_STRING from Lexer:
                        Set is_format_literal to 1
                    End If
                    If fmt_token_kind is equal to TOKEN_VERBATIM_STRING from Lexer:
                        Set is_format_literal to 1
                    End If
                    If fmt_token_kind is equal to TOKEN_TRIPLE_QUOTE_STRING from Lexer:
                        Set is_format_literal to 1
                    End If
                    If is_format_literal is equal to 1:
                        Let fmt_text be proc get_token_text from Lexer with fmt_token
                        proc validate_printf_format_string with analyzer, fmt_text
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let result_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, function_node

    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let arg_node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let arg_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, arg_node
        Set result_type to proc apply_function_type with analyzer, result_type, arg_type
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Introduces each lambda parameter into the already-pushed scope with a
fresh type variable (or the annotated type when the pattern carries one
in its metadata slot) and returns the parameter types in order for
create_function_type to fold. Destructuring parameters bind all their
variables through validate_pattern.
@End Reasoning

Process called "process_lambda_parameters" takes analyzer as Integer, parameter_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Bind lambda parameters and return their types in order

    Let param_types be proc list_create from List

    Let count be proc list_length from List with parameter_list
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let param_node be proc list_get from List with parameter_list, i
        Let param_type be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer

        Let anno be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with param_node, 40
        If anno is not equal to 0:
            Let declared be proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, anno
            proc unify_types with analyzer, param_type, declared
        End If

        proc validate_pattern with analyzer, param_node, param_type
        proc list_append from List with param_types, param_type
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return param_types
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lambda typing over the parser shape (children = parameter patterns then
body last): push a scope, bind parameters with fresh/annotated types,
infer the body in the extended environment, pop, and fold the curried
function type. Parameterless `fun -> e` degenerates to unit -> e via
create_function_type's empty-list rule.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_lambda_type" takes analyzer as Integer, lambda_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a lambda expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lambda_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lambda_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 1:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Lambda expression requires a body"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let body_index be child_count minus 1
    Let parameter_list be proc list_create from List
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than body_index:
        Let param_node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        proc list_append from List with parameter_list, param_node
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc push_scope with analyzer

    Let param_types be proc process_lambda_parameters with analyzer, parameter_list

    Let body_node be proc list_get from List with children, body_index
    Let body_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, body_node

    proc pop_scope with analyzer

    Let function_type be proc create_function_type with analyzer, param_types, body_type

    proc list_destroy from List with parameter_list
    proc list_destroy from List with param_types

    Return function_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
The syntactic-value judgement of the F# value restriction: lambdas,
literals, identifiers, and unit are values, and a TUPLE expression is a
value exactly when every component is - (fun x -> x), 5 is a value while
(f g), 5 is expansive. Applications, control flow, and every other shape
may allocate or observe state and must stay monomorphic.
@End Reasoning

Process called "expr_is_syntactic_value" takes expr_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Decide whether an expression is a syntactic value

    If expr_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let expr_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 0

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_LAMBDA from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If
    If expr_kind is equal to AST_LITERAL from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If
    If expr_kind is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If
    If expr_kind is equal to AST_UNIT from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_TUPLE_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 16
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 24
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let child be proc list_get from List with children, i
            Let child_is_value be proc expr_is_syntactic_value with child
            If child_is_value is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Generalization over a binding pattern: every variable the pattern bound
receives its own scheme computed from ITS OWN component type against the
environment captured before the binding - so let f, n = (fun x -> x), 5
quantifies f's arrow variables while n stays the plain int, exactly how
a single-name let generalizes. Tuple patterns recurse so nested
destructuring (let (f, g), h = ...) generalizes every component.
As-patterns generalize both the inner pattern's variables and the alias.
The bound symbol is read from the innermost table directly (not
lookup_symbol) so the definition itself is not marked used.
@End Reasoning

Process called "generalize_pattern_schemes" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, env_limit as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Attach generalization schemes to a binding pattern's variables

    If pattern_node is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let pattern_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 0

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_VARIABLE from Parser:
        Let pattern_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 8
        Let bound_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with pattern_token
        If bound_name is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let scope_table be proc current_scope_table with analyzer
        Let bound_symbol be proc hashtable_get from Dict with scope_table, bound_name
        If bound_symbol is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let bound_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bound_symbol, 0
        Let scheme be proc generalize with analyzer, bound_type, env_limit
        If scheme is not equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with bound_symbol, 32, scheme
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_TUPLE from Parser:
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let child be proc list_get from List with children, i
            proc generalize_pattern_schemes with analyzer, child, env_limit
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_AS from Parser:
        Set children to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Set child_count to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        Set i to 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Set child to proc list_get from List with children, i
            proc generalize_pattern_schemes with analyzer, child, env_limit
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes one let binding (children [pattern, expression], metadata slot
= optional return-type annotation, value slot = TOKEN_REC tag when
recursive). Recursive bindings pre-bind the pattern against a fresh
variable so the body sees itself, then unify the inferred body type back
into that variable; non-recursive bindings infer first and bind after,
giving correct shadowing. Function bindings (body is a lambda) check the
annotation against the lambda's final return type by walking one
function-arrow step per parameter; value bindings check it against the
whole type.

After inference and annotation checking, the binding is GENERALIZED
under the F# value restriction: syntactic values (lambdas, literals,
identifiers, unit, and tuples of syntactic values) bound to a variable
or tuple pattern quantify their environment-free type variables into a
per-variable scheme via generalize_pattern_schemes; expressions with
possible effects or hidden state (applications, control flow) stay
monomorphic, so let g = f h used at two different types is correctly
rejected while let id = fun x -> x and let f, n = (fun x -> x), 5 check
at every type. The env-types length is captured BEFORE any pattern
binding so a recursive binding's own pre-bound entry never anchors its
variables.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_let_binding_declaration" takes analyzer as Integer, binding_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze one let binding, bind its pattern, and generalize

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with binding_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with binding_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 2:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Let binding requires a pattern and an expression"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let pattern_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    Let expr_node be proc list_get from List with children, 1

    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    Let env_types be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 40
    Let env_limit be proc list_length from List with env_types

    Let rec_flag be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with binding_node, 8
    Let expr_type be 0

    If rec_flag is equal to TOKEN_REC from Lexer:
        Let self_type be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        proc validate_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, self_type
        Set expr_type to proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, expr_node
        Let rec_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, self_type, expr_type
        If rec_ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Recursive binding body disagrees with its own type"
        End If
    Otherwise:
        Set expr_type to proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, expr_node
        proc validate_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, expr_type
    End If

    Let anno be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with binding_node, 40
    If anno is not equal to 0:
        Let declared be proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, anno

        Let expr_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 0
        If expr_kind is equal to AST_LAMBDA from Parser:
            Note: The annotation is the function's return type: walk one
            Note: arrow per parameter to reach it
            Let lambda_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 24
            Let param_count be lambda_count minus 1
            Let walk_type be expr_type
            Let p be 0
            While p is less than param_count:
                Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, walk_type
                Set walk_type to proc get_function_return_type with resolved
                Set p to p plus 1
            End While
            Let anno_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, walk_type, declared
            If anno_ok is equal to 0:
                proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Binding does not match its declared return type"
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set anno_ok to proc unify_types with analyzer, expr_type, declared
            If anno_ok is equal to 0:
                proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Binding does not match its declared type"
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Let-polymorphism: generalize syntactic values bound to a variable
    Note: or tuple pattern (the F# value restriction); each bound variable
    Note: receives a scheme over its OWN component type
    Let pattern_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 0
    Let generalizable_pattern be 0
    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_VARIABLE from Parser:
        Set generalizable_pattern to 1
    End If
    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_TUPLE from Parser:
        Set generalizable_pattern to 1
    End If

    If generalizable_pattern is equal to 1:
        Let is_value be proc expr_is_syntactic_value with expr_node
        If is_value is equal to 1:
            proc generalize_pattern_schemes with analyzer, pattern_node, env_limit
        End If
    End If

    Return expr_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
let-expression typing (children = one or more AST_LET_BINDING nodes from
the and-chain, then an optional trailing body expression from `in`).
Opens a scope so the bindings are local, analyzes each binding, infers
the body in the extended environment, and yields the body type (unit
when no `in` body exists - the statement form).
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_let_type" takes analyzer as Integer, let_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a let expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with let_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with let_node, 24

    proc push_scope with analyzer

    Let result_type be TYPE_UNIT
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let child_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0
        If child_kind is equal to AST_LET_BINDING from Parser:
            proc analyze_let_binding_declaration with analyzer, child
        Otherwise:
            Set result_type to proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc pop_scope with analyzer
    Return result_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
if/elif/else typing: the condition must be bool; with an else (or elif)
branch present both branches unify and the join is the expression's
type; without one the then-branch is statement-positioned and the whole
expression is unit (F# additionally requires the then-branch to BE unit
in that form, so the then type unifies against unit and a mismatch is
reported).
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_if_type" takes analyzer as Integer, if_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of an if expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with if_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with if_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 2:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "If expression requires a condition and a then branch"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let condition_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    Let condition_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, condition_node
    Let cond_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, condition_type, TYPE_BOOL
    If cond_ok is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "If condition must have type bool"
    End If

    Let then_node be proc list_get from List with children, 1
    Let then_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, then_node

    If child_count is greater than 2:
        Let else_node be proc list_get from List with children, 2
        Let else_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, else_node
        Let branch_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, then_type, else_type
        If branch_ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Branches of an if expression must have the same type"
            Return TYPE_ERROR
        End If
        Return then_type
    End If

    Let unit_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, then_type, TYPE_UNIT
    If unit_ok is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "If expression without else must produce unit"
    End If
    Return TYPE_UNIT
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a match expression with its scrutinee type in the solver's
registry. Exhaustiveness runs late (validate_pattern_completeness) so
the scrutinee's type variables have absorbed every constraint the rest
of the program provides before coverage is judged.
@End Reasoning

Process called "register_match_expression" takes analyzer as Integer, match_node as Integer, scrutinee_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Register a match expression for the late completeness pass

    Let pair be proc pool_allocate with analyzer, 16
    If pair is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with pair, 0, match_node
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with pair, 8, scrutinee_type

    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    Let match_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 16
    proc list_append from List with match_registry, pair

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
For each case container (AST_PATTERN_GUARD holding [pattern, body],
where the pattern may itself be guard-wrapped): open a scope, validate
the pattern against the scrutinee type (binding its variables), type a
wrapped guard against bool, infer the body, close the scope, and collect
the body type for the join.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_case_types" takes analyzer as Integer, match_node as Integer, scrutinee_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer the result types of every match case

    Let case_types be proc list_create from List

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with match_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with match_node, 24

    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let case_node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let case_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case_node, 16
        Let case_child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case_node, 24

        If case_child_count is greater than 1:
            proc push_scope with analyzer

            Let pattern_node be proc list_get from List with case_children, 0
            proc validate_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, scrutinee_type

            Let body_node be proc list_get from List with case_children, 1
            Let body_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, body_node
            proc list_append from List with case_types, body_type

            proc pop_scope with analyzer
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return case_types
End Process

@Reasoning:
Computes the join of all case result types by successive unification:
every match arm must produce the same type. Failure reports once and
yields TYPE_ERROR so downstream inference continues. The empty list
(degenerate match) is unit.
@End Reasoning

Process called "find_common_type" takes analyzer as Integer, type_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Join a list of branch types via unification

    Let count be proc list_length from List with type_list
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_UNIT
    End If

    Let result_type be proc list_get from List with type_list, 0
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than count:
        Let next_type be proc list_get from List with type_list, i
        Let ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, result_type, next_type
        If ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "All branches of a match expression must have the same type"
            Return TYPE_ERROR
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Match typing: infer the scrutinee, register the node for late
exhaustiveness analysis, type every case against the scrutinee, and join
the case results.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_match_type" takes analyzer as Integer, match_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a match expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with match_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with match_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 2:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Match expression requires a scrutinee and at least one case"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let scrutinee_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    Let scrutinee_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, scrutinee_node

    proc register_match_expression with analyzer, match_node, scrutinee_type

    Let case_types be proc infer_case_types with analyzer, match_node, scrutinee_type
    Let result_type be proc find_common_type with analyzer, case_types
    proc list_destroy from List with case_types

    Return result_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Tuple typing: infer each component and build the product. Components are
collected into a pooled-record-referencing List that the tuple type
record owns for the analyzer's lifetime.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_tuple_type" takes analyzer as Integer, tuple_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a tuple expression

    Let elem_types be proc list_create from List

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with tuple_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with tuple_node, 24
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let elem_node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let elem_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, elem_node
        proc list_append from List with elem_types, elem_type
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_TUPLE, elem_types
End Process

@Reasoning:
Homogeneous-collection typing shared by lists and arrays: every element
unifies with the first (mismatches report once per offending element);
the element type of an empty literal is a fresh variable that later
usage constrains.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_collection_type" takes analyzer as Integer, coll_node as Integer, type_tag_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a homogeneous collection literal

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with coll_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with coll_node, 24

    Let elem_type be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let elem_node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let this_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, elem_node
        Let ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, elem_type, this_type
        If ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "All elements of a collection must have the same type"
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, type_tag_value, elem_type
End Process

Process called "infer_list_type" takes analyzer as Integer, list_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a list literal
    Return proc infer_collection_type with analyzer, list_node, TYPE_LIST
End Process

Process called "infer_array_type" takes analyzer as Integer, array_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of an array literal
    Return proc infer_collection_type with analyzer, array_node, TYPE_ARRAY
End Process

@Reasoning:
Record-expression typing over the parser shape (each field child is an
AST_LET_BINDING whose value slot holds the field-name token and whose
single child is the field's value expression): infers every field value
and reports duplicate field names - the structural error decidable
without nominal field tables. The result is an anonymous record type
(name 0) that unifies with any named record, because F# resolves the
nominal record from field names across modules this analysis cannot see.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_record_type" takes analyzer as Integer, record_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a record expression

    Let seen_names be proc list_create from List

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with record_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with record_node, 24
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let field_node be proc list_get from List with children, i

        Let field_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with field_node, 8
        Let field_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with field_token
        If field_name is not equal to 0:
            Let seen_count be proc list_length from List with seen_names
            Let s be 0
            While s is less than seen_count:
                Let prior be proc list_get from List with seen_names, s
                Let same be proc string_equals from StringCore with prior, field_name
                If same is equal to 1:
                    Let message be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Duplicate record field: ", field_name
                    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, message
                End If
                Set s to s plus 1
            End While
            proc list_append from List with seen_names, field_name
        End If

        Let field_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with field_node, 16
        Let field_child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with field_node, 24
        If field_child_count is greater than 0:
            Let value_node be proc list_get from List with field_children, 0
            proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, value_node
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc list_destroy from List with seen_names
    Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_RECORD, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sequence-expression typing: every child is evaluated for effect except
the last, whose type is the sequence's value. Empty sequences are unit.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_sequence_type" takes analyzer as Integer, seq_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a sequence expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with seq_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with seq_node, 24

    Let result_type be TYPE_UNIT
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Set result_type to proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
try/with/finally typing over the parser shape (child 0 = protected body,
AST_PATTERN_GUARD children = handler arms, trailing non-guard child =
finally expression): every handler body unifies with the protected
body's type because either path produces the expression's value; handler
patterns bind in their own scope against TYPE_ANY (the exception value -
System.Exception-derived, outside this module's type knowledge); the
finally expression is effect-positioned.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_try_type" takes analyzer as Integer, try_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a try expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with try_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with try_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 1:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Try expression requires a body"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let body_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    Let body_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, body_node

    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let child_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_GUARD from Parser:
            Let handler_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 16
            Let handler_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 24
            If handler_count is greater than 1:
                proc push_scope with analyzer

                Let pattern_node be proc list_get from List with handler_children, 0
                proc validate_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, TYPE_ANY

                Let handler_body be proc list_get from List with handler_children, 1
                Let handler_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, handler_body
                Let ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, body_type, handler_type
                If ok is equal to 0:
                    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Exception handler must have the same type as the try body"
                End If

                proc pop_scope with analyzer
            End If
        Otherwise:
            proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, child
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return body_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
while-loop typing: the condition must be bool and the loop produces
unit. The body is inferred for nested diagnostics.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_while_type" takes analyzer as Integer, while_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a while expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with while_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with while_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 2:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "While expression requires a condition and a body"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let condition_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    Let condition_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, condition_node
    Let cond_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, condition_type, TYPE_BOOL
    If cond_ok is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "While condition must have type bool"
    End If

    Let body_node be proc list_get from List with children, 1
    proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, body_node

    Return TYPE_UNIT
End Process

@Reasoning:
for-loop typing over the parser shape (children [iteration variable
pattern, iterable, body]): the loop variable binds in a fresh scope; an
iterable that is a known sequence shape (list/array/seq) constrains the
variable to its element type, an integer range (the range operator
produces int seq) constrains it to int, and anything else leaves the
variable free. For loops produce unit.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_for_type" takes analyzer as Integer, for_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a for expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with for_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with for_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 3:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "For expression requires a variable, an iterable, and a body"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let iterable_node be proc list_get from List with children, 1
    Let iterable_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, iterable_node

    Let elem_type be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, iterable_type
    Let tag be proc type_tag with resolved

    Let is_sequence_shape be 0
    If tag is equal to TYPE_LIST:
        Set is_sequence_shape to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ARRAY:
        Set is_sequence_shape to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_SEQUENCE:
        Set is_sequence_shape to 1
    End If

    If is_sequence_shape is equal to 1:
        Let inner be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        proc unify_types with analyzer, elem_type, inner
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_INT:
        Note: for i = a to b iterates integers
        proc unify_types with analyzer, elem_type, TYPE_INT
    End If

    proc push_scope with analyzer

    Let var_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    proc validate_pattern with analyzer, var_node, elem_type

    Let body_node be proc list_get from List with children, 2
    proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, body_node

    proc pop_scope with analyzer

    Return TYPE_UNIT
End Process

@Reasoning:
Pipe typing over the parser shape (value slot = pipe operator's token
TYPE TAG, children [left, right]): x |> f applies f to x, f <| x applies
f to x. Both reduce to one apply_function_type step, so pipes get the
same inference quality as direct application.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_pipe_type" takes analyzer as Integer, pipe_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of a pipeline expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pipe_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pipe_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 2:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Pipeline requires two operands"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let left_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    Let right_node be proc list_get from List with children, 1
    Let left_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, left_node
    Let right_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, right_node

    Let operator be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pipe_node, 8
    If operator is equal to TOKEN_PIPE_RIGHT from Lexer:
        Return proc apply_function_type with analyzer, right_type, left_type
    End If
    If operator is equal to TOKEN_PIPE_LEFT from Lexer:
        Return proc apply_function_type with analyzer, left_type, right_type
    End If

    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Unknown pipeline operator"
    Return TYPE_ERROR
End Process

@Reasoning:
The printf-family invalid-combination table, exactly as F#'s format
checker (CheckFormatStrings) enforces over %[flags][width][.precision]
type with the type letters b c d i u x X o s f F e E g G M A O:
- the '#' modifier is invalid in F# with EVERY specifier;
- the '0' zero-padding flag is invalid with the non-numeric specifiers
  %b %c %s %O and with %A;
- the '+' and ' ' numeric-prefix flags are invalid with %b %c %s %O;
  %A accepts '+' (structured plus signs) but not ' ';
- precision is valid ONLY with the floating/decimal family
  %f %F %e %E %g %G %M - integer and non-numeric specifiers reject it;
- '-' (left justify) and width are valid with every specifier.
One shared checker keeps interpolated-hole validation and printf-family
format-string validation on the identical table.
@End Reasoning

Process called "check_spec_combination" takes analyzer as Integer, has_zero as Integer, has_plus as Integer, has_space as Integer, has_hash as Integer, has_precision as Integer, type_ch as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Apply the F# flag/specifier invalid-combination table

    If has_hash is equal to 1:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "The # formatting modifier is invalid in F#"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_non_numeric be 0
    If type_ch is equal to 98:  Note: 'b'
        Set is_non_numeric to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 99:  Note: 'c'
        Set is_non_numeric to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 115:  Note: 's'
        Set is_non_numeric to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 79:  Note: 'O'
        Set is_non_numeric to 1
    End If

    If is_non_numeric is equal to 1:
        If has_zero is equal to 1:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "The '0' padding flag is invalid with a non-numeric format specifier"
            Return 0
        End If
        If has_plus is equal to 1:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "The '+' prefix flag is invalid with a non-numeric format specifier"
            Return 0
        End If
        If has_space is equal to 1:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "The ' ' prefix flag is invalid with a non-numeric format specifier"
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    If type_ch is equal to 65:  Note: 'A'
        If has_zero is equal to 1:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "The '0' padding flag is invalid with %A"
            Return 0
        End If
        If has_space is equal to 1:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "The ' ' prefix flag is invalid with %A"
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    If has_precision is equal to 1:
        Let precision_ok be 0
        If type_ch is equal to 102:  Note: 'f'
            Set precision_ok to 1
        End If
        If type_ch is equal to 70:   Note: 'F'
            Set precision_ok to 1
        End If
        If type_ch is equal to 101:  Note: 'e'
            Set precision_ok to 1
        End If
        If type_ch is equal to 69:   Note: 'E'
            Set precision_ok to 1
        End If
        If type_ch is equal to 103:  Note: 'g'
            Set precision_ok to 1
        End If
        If type_ch is equal to 71:   Note: 'G'
            Set precision_ok to 1
        End If
        If type_ch is equal to 77:   Note: 'M'
            Set precision_ok to 1
        End If
        If precision_ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "A precision is not valid with this format specifier"
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses one %specifier beginning at the '%' byte and validates it against
the combination table. Returns the position just past the type character
on success and -1 on error (the diagnostic is already recorded), so the
format-string scanner can resume after each specifier. An unknown type
letter is itself an error - printf rejects undefined specifiers
statically.
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_printf_spec_at" takes analyzer as Integer, text as Integer, start as Integer, text_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate one printf specifier; return end position or -1

    Let i be start plus 1
    Let has_zero be 0
    Let has_plus be 0
    Let has_space be 0
    Let has_hash be 0

    Let scanning_flags be 1
    While scanning_flags is equal to 1:
        If i is greater than or equal to text_len:
            Set scanning_flags to 0
            Continue
        End If
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        Let is_flag be 0
        If ch is equal to 43:  Note: '+'
            Set has_plus to 1
            Set is_flag to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 45:  Note: '-'
            Set is_flag to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 32:  Note: ' '
            Set has_space to 1
            Set is_flag to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 48:  Note: '0'
            Set has_zero to 1
            Set is_flag to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 35:  Note: '#'
            Set has_hash to 1
            Set is_flag to 1
        End If
        If is_flag is equal to 1:
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set scanning_flags to 0
        End If
    End While

    While i is less than text_len:
        Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        Let is_width_digit be 0
        If ch is greater than or equal to 48:
            If ch is less than or equal to 57:
                Set is_width_digit to 1
            End If
        End If
        If is_width_digit is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let has_precision be 0
    If i is less than text_len:
        Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        If ch is equal to 46:  Note: '.'
            Set has_precision to 1
            Set i to i plus 1
            While i is less than text_len:
                Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
                Let is_prec_digit be 0
                If ch is greater than or equal to 48:
                    If ch is less than or equal to 57:
                        Set is_prec_digit to 1
                    End If
                End If
                If is_prec_digit is equal to 0:
                    Break
                End If
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    If i is greater than or equal to text_len:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Incomplete printf format specifier"
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If

    Let type_ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
    Let is_type be 0
    If type_ch is equal to 98:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 99:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 100:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 105:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 117:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 120:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 88:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 111:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 115:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 102:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 70:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 101:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 69:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 103:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 71:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 77:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 65:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If
    If type_ch is equal to 79:
        Set is_type to 1
    End If

    If is_type is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Invalid printf format specifier"
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If

    Let combo_ok be proc check_spec_combination with analyzer, has_zero, has_plus, has_space, has_hash, has_precision, type_ch
    If combo_ok is equal to 0:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If

    Return i plus 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Scans a printf-family format-string literal and validates every
%specifier against the combination table. %% is the literal-percent
escape and is skipped. Returns 1 when every specifier is valid; errors
are recorded per offending specifier and scanning continues so one bad
specifier does not hide the next.
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_printf_format_string" takes analyzer as Integer, fmt as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate every %specifier in a printf-family format string

    If fmt is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let fmt_len be proc string_length from StringCore with fmt
    Let all_ok be 1
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than fmt_len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with fmt, i
        If ch is equal to 37:  Note: '%'
            Let next_i be i plus 1
            If next_i is less than fmt_len:
                Let next_ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with fmt, next_i
                If next_ch is equal to 37:  Note: %% escape
                    Set i to i plus 2
                    Continue
                End If
            End If
            Let end_pos be proc validate_printf_spec_at with analyzer, fmt, i, fmt_len
            If end_pos is less than 0:
                Set all_ok to 0
                Set i to i plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set i to end_pos
            End If
            Continue
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return all_ok
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates the format specification attached to one interpolation hole.
The lexer preserves both spellings losslessly: a printf-style specifier
captured before the hole arrives first ("%d"), and a .NET-style
alignment/format suffix captured inside the hole arrives with its
leading separator (",10", ":F2", ",10:F2"). F# forbids COMBINING the
two on one hole - %d{x,10} is the alignment+specifier combination the
compiler rejects - so a spec that starts with '%' must end exactly at
its type character. Pure .NET alignment must be an optional '-' followed
by digits (F# requires a constant integer alignment); the :format text
is free-form and validated by the runtime formatter.
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_hole_format_spec" takes analyzer as Integer, spec as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate one interpolation hole's format specification

    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let spec_len be proc string_length from StringCore with spec
    If spec_len is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let first be proc string_char_at from StringCore with spec, 0

    If first is equal to 37:  Note: '%' printf-style specifier
        Let end_pos be proc validate_printf_spec_at with analyzer, spec, 0, spec_len
        If end_pos is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        If end_pos is less than spec_len:
            Let combo_message be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "A printf-style format specifier cannot be combined with .NET-style alignment or format text in an interpolated string hole: ", spec
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, combo_message
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If first is equal to 44:  Note: ',' .NET alignment
        Let i be 1
        If i is less than spec_len:
            Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with spec, i
            If ch is equal to 45:  Note: '-'
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        End If
        Let digit_count be 0
        Let scanning_digits be 1
        While scanning_digits is equal to 1:
            If i is greater than or equal to spec_len:
                Set scanning_digits to 0
                Continue
            End If
            Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with spec, i
            If ch is greater than or equal to 48:
                If ch is less than or equal to 57:
                    Set digit_count to digit_count plus 1
                    Set i to i plus 1
                    Continue
                End If
            End If
            Set scanning_digits to 0
        End While

        If digit_count is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Invalid alignment in interpolated string hole"
            Return 0
        End If
        If i is less than spec_len:
            Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with spec, i
            If ch is not equal to 58:  Note: only a ':' format may follow
                proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Invalid alignment in interpolated string hole"
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If first is equal to 58:  Note: ':' .NET format text - runtime-validated
        Return 1
    End If

    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Malformed format specification in interpolated string hole"
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Interpolated strings type as string. Hole expressions are inferred for
their own diagnostics but accept any type (F# formats holes through %O /
ToString), and literal segment children are string by construction. The
parser's child layout is positional - child 0 is the leading literal
segment, then [hole expression, literal segment] pairs - so the odd
indices are exactly the holes; each hole's metadata slot (offset 40)
carries its format specification when one was written, validated here
against the F# combination rules.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_interpolated_type" takes analyzer as Integer, interp_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of an interpolated string

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with interp_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with interp_node, 24
    Let i be 0
    Let is_hole be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc list_get from List with children, i
        proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, child

        If is_hole is equal to 1:
            Let hole_spec be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 40
            If hole_spec is not equal to 0:
                proc validate_hole_format_spec with analyzer, hole_spec
            End If
            Set is_hole to 0
        Otherwise:
            Set is_hole to 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return TYPE_STRING
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Computation, Async, and Measure Analysis
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Builder-method admissibility for the AST_COMPUTATION_EXPRESSION shape
(children [builder, body]). A primitive-typed builder can never carry
Bind/Return members, so primitives are rejected outright; the known
monadic shapes (async/seq/computation) are accepted; record-typed,
obj-typed, and free-variable builders are accepted because member
verification for them requires .NET metadata that a source-level
translation frontend does not possess - this check rejects exactly what
is provably wrong from source alone.
@End Reasoning

Process called "builder_has_method" takes analyzer as Integer, builder_type as Integer, method_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Decide whether a builder type can carry the named method

    Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, builder_type
    Let tag be proc type_tag with resolved

    Let is_primitive be 0
    If tag is equal to TYPE_INT:
        Set is_primitive to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_FLOAT:
        Set is_primitive to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_STRING:
        Set is_primitive to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_BOOL:
        Set is_primitive to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_CHAR:
        Set is_primitive to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_UNIT:
        Set is_primitive to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_BYTE:
        Set is_primitive to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_DECIMAL:
        Set is_primitive to 1
    End If

    If is_primitive is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Computation bodies open their own scope (let! / use! bindings are local
to the builder body); the builder context needs no extra analyzer state
because builder-specific typing happens at the builder_has_method gate.
@End Reasoning

Process called "push_computation_scope" takes analyzer as Integer, builder_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Open the computation-expression body scope
    Return proc push_scope with analyzer
End Process

Process called "analyze_computation_body" takes analyzer as Integer, body_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer the type of a computation-expression body
    Return proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, body_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Computation expressions (builder { body }) validate that the builder can
carry Bind and Return, then type the body in its own scope and wrap the
result in the computation shape so consumers see M<T> rather than T.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_computation_expression" takes analyzer as Integer, comp_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze a computation expression

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with comp_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with comp_node, 24
    If child_count is less than 2:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Computation expression requires a builder and a body"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let builder_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
    Let builder_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, builder_node

    Let has_bind be proc builder_has_method with analyzer, builder_type, "Bind"
    If has_bind is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Computation builder cannot carry a Bind method"
    End If
    Let has_return be proc builder_has_method with analyzer, builder_type, "Return"
    If has_return is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Computation builder cannot carry a Return method"
    End If

    proc push_computation_scope with analyzer, builder_type

    Let body_node be proc list_get from List with children, 1
    Let body_type be proc analyze_computation_body with analyzer, body_node

    proc pop_scope with analyzer

    Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_COMPUTATION, body_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Async expressions are the Async-builder special case: the body types in
its own scope and the result wraps as Async<'T>.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_async_body" takes async_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the body expression of an async node

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with async_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with async_node, 24
    If child_count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc list_get from List with children, 0
End Process

Process called "push_async_scope" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Open the async body scope
    Return proc push_scope with analyzer
End Process

Process called "create_async_type" takes analyzer as Integer, body_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Wrap a type as Async of that type
    Return proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_ASYNC, body_type
End Process

Process called "analyze_async_expression" takes analyzer as Integer, async_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze an async expression

    Let async_body be proc get_async_body with async_node
    If async_body is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Async expression requires a body"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    proc push_async_scope with analyzer
    Let body_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, async_body
    proc pop_scope with analyzer

    Return proc create_async_type with analyzer, body_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Units-of-measure accessors over the AST_MEASURE shape (value slot = unit
name token, child 0 = magnitude expression).
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_measure_value" takes measure_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the magnitude expression of a measure node

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with measure_expr, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with measure_expr, 24
    If child_count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc list_get from List with children, 0
End Process

Process called "get_measure_unit" takes measure_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the unit name of a measure node

    Let unit_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with measure_expr, 8
    Return proc get_token_text from Lexer with unit_token
End Process

Process called "lookup_measure_unit" takes analyzer as Integer, measure_unit as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Look up a declared measure unit

    If measure_unit is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let measure_system be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 56
    Return proc hashtable_get from Dict with measure_system, measure_unit
End Process

Process called "create_measured_type" takes analyzer as Integer, base_type as Integer, measure_unit as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a measured numeric type

    Return proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_MEASURE, base_type, measure_unit
End Process

@Reasoning:
Measure analysis: the unit must be declared (undeclared units are the
"Unknown unit of measure" error, F#'s behaviour for missing [<Measure>]
declarations), and the magnitude must be numeric (int, float, decimal, a
still-free variable that then constrains to float - F#'s default measure
carrier - or obj). The result is the measured wrapper type whose
unification rule demands matching units.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_units_of_measure" takes analyzer as Integer, measure_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze a units-of-measure expression

    Let measure_unit be proc get_measure_unit with measure_expr
    Let unit_info be proc lookup_measure_unit with analyzer, measure_unit
    If unit_info is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Unknown unit of measure"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Let magnitude_node be proc get_measure_value with measure_expr
    Let base_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, magnitude_node

    Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, base_type
    Let tag be proc type_tag with resolved

    Let is_numeric be 0
    If tag is equal to TYPE_INT:
        Set is_numeric to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_FLOAT:
        Set is_numeric to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_DECIMAL:
        Set is_numeric to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ANY:
        Set is_numeric to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        proc unify_types with analyzer, resolved, TYPE_FLOAT
        Set is_numeric to 1
    End If

    If is_numeric is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Units of measure apply only to numeric values"
        Return TYPE_ERROR
    End If

    Return proc create_measured_type with analyzer, base_type, measure_unit
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expression Dispatcher
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The inference dispatcher over the REAL parser node kinds: one AST_LITERAL
kind discriminated by token class (not per-literal AST kinds), match/if/
let/try/while/for under their *_EXPRESSION names, AST_UNIT for (), pipe
nodes carrying operator tags, wildcards in expression position (the F#
shorthand-argument form) as fresh variables, and quotations typing their
inner expression then yielding obj (Expr<'T> is a .NET reflection type
outside this module's knowledge). Unknown kinds are TYPE_UNKNOWN rather
than errors so one unexpected shape cannot cascade.
@End Reasoning

Process called "infer_expression_type" takes analyzer as Integer, expr_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer the type of an F# expression node

    If expr_node is equal to 0:
        Return TYPE_UNIT
    End If

    Let expr_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 0

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_LITERAL from Parser:
        Let literal_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 8
        Return proc literal_token_type with literal_token
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_UNIT from Parser:
        Return TYPE_UNIT
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
        Return proc infer_identifier_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_APPLICATION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_application_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_LAMBDA from Parser:
        Return proc infer_lambda_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_LET_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_let_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_MATCH_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_match_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_IF_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_if_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_TUPLE_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_tuple_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_LIST_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_list_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_ARRAY_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_array_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_RECORD_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_record_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_SEQUENCE_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_sequence_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_TRY_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_try_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_WHILE_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_while_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_FOR_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_for_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_PIPE_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_pipe_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_INTERPOLATED_STRING from Parser:
        Return proc infer_interpolated_type with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_COMPUTATION_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc analyze_computation_expression with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_MEASURE from Parser:
        Return proc analyze_units_of_measure with analyzer, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_QUOTE_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Let quote_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 16
        Let quote_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with expr_node, 24
        If quote_count is greater than 0:
            Let inner be proc list_get from List with quote_children, 0
            proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, inner
        End If
        Return TYPE_ANY
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_WILDCARD from Parser:
        Return proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    End If

    Return TYPE_UNKNOWN
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pattern Validation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Constructor-pattern checking: built-in option/Result constructors get
per-use polymorphic handling (Some x constrains the scrutinee to
'a option and binds x at 'a; Ok/Error constrain to the Result union and
bind payloads fresh), declared constructors constrain the scrutinee to
their owning union and check the payload sub-pattern against the
declared payload type (tuple payloads destructure componentwise; nullary
constructors with arguments are an arity error), and unknown
constructors - cross-module union cases this single-file analysis cannot
see - bind their sub-patterns against fresh variables without error,
because rejecting them would false-positive on every interop match.
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_constructor_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate a constructor pattern against the expected type

    Let ctor_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 8
    Let ctor_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with ctor_token
    If ctor_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24

    Let is_some be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Some"
    If is_some is equal to 1:
        Let elem be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Let option_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_OPTION, elem
        Let ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, expected_type, option_type
        If ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Pattern type mismatch: Some applies to option values"
            Return 0
        End If
        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let payload_pattern be proc list_get from List with children, 0
            Return proc validate_pattern with analyzer, payload_pattern, elem
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_none be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "None"
    If is_none is equal to 1:
        Set elem to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        Set option_type to proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_OPTION, elem
        Set ok to proc unify_types with analyzer, expected_type, option_type
        If ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Pattern type mismatch: None applies to option values"
            Return 0
        End If
        If child_count is greater than 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Constructor None takes no arguments"
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_ok_ctor be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Ok"
    Let is_err_ctor be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_name, "Error"
    Let is_result be 0
    If is_ok_ctor is equal to 1:
        Set is_result to 1
    End If
    If is_err_ctor is equal to 1:
        Set is_result to 1
    End If
    If is_result is equal to 1:
        Let result_cases be proc list_create from List
        proc list_append from List with result_cases, "Ok"
        proc list_append from List with result_cases, "Error"
        Let result_union be proc make_type2 with analyzer, TYPE_UNION, "Result", result_cases
        Set ok to proc unify_types with analyzer, expected_type, result_union
        If ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Pattern type mismatch: Ok/Error apply to Result values"
            Return 0
        End If
        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Set payload_pattern to proc list_get from List with children, 0
            Set elem to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
            Return proc validate_pattern with analyzer, payload_pattern, elem
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Let ctor_info be proc lookup_constructor with analyzer, ctor_name
    If ctor_info is equal to 0:
        Note: Cross-module constructor: bind sub-patterns against fresh types
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let sub_pattern be proc list_get from List with children, i
            Let sub_type be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
            proc validate_pattern with analyzer, sub_pattern, sub_type
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Let union_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ctor_info, 0
    Set ok to proc unify_types with analyzer, expected_type, union_type
    If ok is equal to 0:
        Let message be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Pattern type mismatch for constructor: ", ctor_name
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, message
        Return 0
    End If

    Let has_payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ctor_info, 16
    If has_payload is equal to 0:
        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Set message to proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Constructor takes no arguments: ", ctor_name
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, message
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Let payload_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ctor_info, 8

    If child_count is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    If child_count is equal to 1:
        Set payload_pattern to proc list_get from List with children, 0
        Return proc validate_pattern with analyzer, payload_pattern, payload_type
    End If

    Note: Multiple sub-patterns destructure a tuple payload componentwise
    Let resolved_payload be proc resolve_type with analyzer, payload_type
    Let payload_tag be proc type_tag with resolved_payload
    If payload_tag is equal to TYPE_TUPLE:
        Let elems be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved_payload, 8
        Let elem_count be proc list_length from List with elems
        If elem_count is not equal to child_count:
            Set message to proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Constructor pattern arity mismatch: ", ctor_name
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, message
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to 0
        Let all_ok be 1
        While i is less than child_count:
            Set sub_pattern to proc list_get from List with children, i
            Let elem_type be proc list_get from List with elems, i
            Set ok to proc validate_pattern with analyzer, sub_pattern, elem_type
            If ok is equal to 0:
                Set all_ok to 0
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return all_ok
    End If

    Set i to 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Set sub_pattern to proc list_get from List with children, i
        Set sub_type to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
        proc validate_pattern with analyzer, sub_pattern, sub_type
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Tuple-pattern checking: a tuple-typed scrutinee must agree in arity and
each component validates against its component type; a free-variable
scrutinee learns the tuple shape (fresh component variables); obj/error
scrutinees validate components freshly; any other concrete type is a
shape mismatch.
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_tuple_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate a tuple pattern against the expected type

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24

    Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, expected_type
    Let tag be proc type_tag with resolved

    If tag is equal to TYPE_TUPLE:
        Let elems be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 8
        Let elem_count be proc list_length from List with elems
        If elem_count is not equal to child_count:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Tuple pattern arity mismatch"
            Return 0
        End If
        Let i be 0
        Let all_ok be 1
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let sub_pattern be proc list_get from List with children, i
            Let elem_type be proc list_get from List with elems, i
            Let ok be proc validate_pattern with analyzer, sub_pattern, elem_type
            If ok is equal to 0:
                Set all_ok to 0
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return all_ok
    End If

    If tag is equal to TYPE_GENERIC:
        Let fresh_elems be proc list_create from List
        Set i to 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let fresh_elem be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
            proc list_append from List with fresh_elems, fresh_elem
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Let tuple_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_TUPLE, fresh_elems
        proc unify_types with analyzer, resolved, tuple_type
        Set i to 0
        Set all_ok to 1
        While i is less than child_count:
            Set sub_pattern to proc list_get from List with children, i
            Set elem_type to proc list_get from List with fresh_elems, i
            Set ok to proc validate_pattern with analyzer, sub_pattern, elem_type
            If ok is equal to 0:
                Set all_ok to 0
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return all_ok
    End If

    Let is_open be 0
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ANY:
        Set is_open to 1
    End If
    If tag is equal to TYPE_ERROR:
        Set is_open to 1
    End If
    If is_open is equal to 1:
        Set i to 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Set sub_pattern to proc list_get from List with children, i
            Set elem_type to proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
            proc validate_pattern with analyzer, sub_pattern, elem_type
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Tuple pattern applied to a non-tuple value"
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Element-sequence pattern checking shared by lists and arrays: the
scrutinee constrains to the matching collection of a (possibly fresh)
element type and every element pattern validates against that element
type.
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_sequence_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, expected_type as Integer, type_tag_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate a list/array pattern against the expected type

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24

    Let elem_type be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
    Let coll_type be proc make_type1 with analyzer, type_tag_value, elem_type
    Let ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, expected_type, coll_type
    If ok is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Collection pattern applied to a non-collection value"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let i be 0
    Let all_ok be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let sub_pattern be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Set ok to proc validate_pattern with analyzer, sub_pattern, elem_type
        If ok is equal to 0:
            Set all_ok to 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return all_ok
End Process

Process called "validate_list_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate a list pattern
    Return proc validate_sequence_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, expected_type, TYPE_LIST
End Process

Process called "validate_array_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate an array pattern
    Return proc validate_sequence_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, expected_type, TYPE_ARRAY
End Process

@Reasoning:
Record-pattern checking over the parser shape (each field child is an
AST_PATTERN_VARIABLE whose value slot is the field-name token and whose
single child is the sub-pattern): duplicate field names report, every
sub-pattern binds against a fresh type, and the scrutinee constrains to
an anonymous record (nominal field typing requires the cross-module
record tables F# resolves at assembly level).
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_record_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate a record pattern against the expected type

    Let anon_record be proc make_type1 with analyzer, TYPE_RECORD, 0
    Let ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, expected_type, anon_record
    If ok is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Record pattern applied to a non-record value"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let seen_names be proc list_create from List

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
    Let i be 0
    Let all_ok be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let field_node be proc list_get from List with children, i

        Let field_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with field_node, 8
        Let field_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with field_token
        If field_name is not equal to 0:
            Let seen_count be proc list_length from List with seen_names
            Let s be 0
            While s is less than seen_count:
                Let prior be proc list_get from List with seen_names, s
                Let same be proc string_equals from StringCore with prior, field_name
                If same is equal to 1:
                    Let message be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Duplicate field in record pattern: ", field_name
                    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, message
                    Set all_ok to 0
                End If
                Set s to s plus 1
            End While
            proc list_append from List with seen_names, field_name
        End If

        Let field_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with field_node, 16
        Let field_child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with field_node, 24
        If field_child_count is greater than 0:
            Let sub_pattern be proc list_get from List with field_children, 0
            Let sub_type be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
            Let sub_ok be proc validate_pattern with analyzer, sub_pattern, sub_type
            If sub_ok is equal to 0:
                Set all_ok to 0
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc list_destroy from List with seen_names
    Return all_ok
End Process

@Reasoning:
The pattern dispatcher: validates one pattern against the scrutinee type
and binds every variable the pattern introduces. Wildcards always match;
variables bind at the expected type (honouring an annotation in the
metadata slot); literals must be type-compatible (checked through
unification so a free scrutinee learns the literal's type); as/or/guard
wrappers recurse with the appropriate extra obligations (or-patterns
validate EVERY alternative against the same type so alternative
mismatches surface; guards must be bool); composite shapes route to
their dedicated validators; type-test patterns bind their as-binder at
the tested type; active patterns bind sub-patterns freshly (banks of
active-pattern definitions are cross-module).
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate a pattern against an expected type, binding variables

    If pattern_node is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let pattern_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 0

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_WILDCARD from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_VARIABLE from Parser:
        Let var_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 8
        Let var_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with var_token

        Let bind_type be expected_type
        Let anno be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 40
        If anno is not equal to 0:
            Let declared be proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, anno
            Let anno_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, expected_type, declared
            If anno_ok is equal to 0:
                proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Pattern annotation disagrees with the matched value"
            End If
            Set bind_type to declared
        End If

        proc add_pattern_variable with analyzer, var_name, bind_type
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_LITERAL from Parser:
        Let literal_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 8
        Let literal_type be proc literal_token_type with literal_token
        Let lit_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, literal_type, expected_type
        If lit_ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Literal pattern type mismatch"
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_AS from Parser:
        Let as_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Let as_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        If as_count is less than 2:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let inner_pattern be proc list_get from List with as_children, 0
        Let inner_ok be proc validate_pattern with analyzer, inner_pattern, expected_type
        Let alias_pattern be proc list_get from List with as_children, 1
        Let alias_ok be proc validate_pattern with analyzer, alias_pattern, expected_type
        If inner_ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return alias_ok
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_OR from Parser:
        Let or_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Let or_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        Let i be 0
        Let all_ok be 1
        While i is less than or_count:
            Let alternative be proc list_get from List with or_children, i
            Let alt_ok be proc validate_pattern with analyzer, alternative, expected_type
            If alt_ok is equal to 0:
                Set all_ok to 0
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return all_ok
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_GUARD from Parser:
        Let guard_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Let guard_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        If guard_count is less than 2:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set inner_pattern to proc list_get from List with guard_children, 0
        Set inner_ok to proc validate_pattern with analyzer, inner_pattern, expected_type

        Let guard_expr be proc list_get from List with guard_children, 1
        Let guard_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, guard_expr
        Let guard_ok be proc unify_types with analyzer, guard_type, TYPE_BOOL
        If guard_ok is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Pattern guard must have type bool"
        End If
        Return inner_ok
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_CONSTRUCTOR from Parser:
        Return proc validate_constructor_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, expected_type
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_TUPLE from Parser:
        Return proc validate_tuple_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, expected_type
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_LIST from Parser:
        Return proc validate_list_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, expected_type
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_ARRAY from Parser:
        Return proc validate_array_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, expected_type
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_RECORD from Parser:
        Return proc validate_record_pattern with analyzer, pattern_node, expected_type
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_TYPE_TEST from Parser:
        Let type_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 8
        Let tested_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with type_token
        Let tested_type be proc resolve_type_name with analyzer, tested_name

        Let test_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Let test_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        If test_count is greater than 0:
            Let binder be proc list_get from List with test_children, 0
            Return proc validate_pattern with analyzer, binder, tested_type
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_ACTIVE from Parser:
        Let active_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Let active_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        Set i to 0
        While i is less than active_count:
            Let active_sub be proc list_get from List with active_children, i
            Let active_type be proc fresh_type_var with analyzer
            proc validate_pattern with analyzer, active_sub, active_type
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Unsupported pattern shape"
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Match Exhaustiveness Analysis
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Irrefutability decides coverage without type knowledge: wildcards and
bare variables always match; an as-pattern is irrefutable when its inner
pattern is; an or-pattern is when ANY alternative is; a tuple pattern is
when ALL components are. Guarded patterns are never irrefutable (the
guard can fail at runtime). Everything else (literals, constructors,
collections, records, type tests) is refutable.
@End Reasoning

Process called "pattern_is_irrefutable" takes pattern_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Decide whether a pattern matches every value of its type

    If pattern_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pattern_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 0

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_WILDCARD from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If
    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_VARIABLE from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_AS from Parser:
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let inner be proc list_get from List with children, 0
            Return proc pattern_is_irrefutable with inner
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_OR from Parser:
        Set children to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Set child_count to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let alternative be proc list_get from List with children, i
            Let covered be proc pattern_is_irrefutable with alternative
            If covered is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 0
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_TUPLE from Parser:
        Set children to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Set child_count to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        Set i to 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let component be proc list_get from List with children, i
            Set covered to proc pattern_is_irrefutable with component
            If covered is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
String-membership helper for the coverage name lists (constructor names,
union case names). Linear scan with string_equals; coverage lists are
small (the arm count of one match).
@End Reasoning

Process called "name_list_contains" takes name_list as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether a name list contains a string

    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with name_list
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let candidate be proc list_get from List with name_list, i
        Let same be proc string_equals from StringCore with candidate, name
        If same is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Collects one unguarded arm pattern's contribution to coverage:
constructor names append to the covered-name list (or-patterns
contribute every alternative), and bool literal patterns raise the
true/false flags through a 16-byte flag record the caller owns. Guarded
arms never contribute (the guard can decline the value).
@End Reasoning

Process called "collect_pattern_coverage" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern_node as Integer, covered_names as Integer, bool_flags as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Record one pattern's coverage contribution

    If pattern_node is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let pattern_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 0

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_CONSTRUCTOR from Parser:
        Let ctor_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 8
        Let ctor_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with ctor_token
        If ctor_name is not equal to 0:
            proc list_append from List with covered_names, ctor_name
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_LITERAL from Parser:
        Let literal_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 8
        Let token_kind be proc get_token_type from Lexer with literal_token
        If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_TRUE from Lexer:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with bool_flags, 0, 1
        End If
        If token_kind is equal to TOKEN_FALSE from Lexer:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with bool_flags, 8, 1
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_OR from Parser:
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let alternative be proc list_get from List with children, i
            proc collect_pattern_coverage with analyzer, alternative, covered_names, bool_flags
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_AS from Parser:
        Set children to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
        Set child_count to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let inner be proc list_get from List with children, 0
            Return proc collect_pattern_coverage with analyzer, inner, covered_names, bool_flags
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Per-match exhaustiveness and redundancy. Walks the arms in order: an arm
positioned after coverage is already total is redundant ("This rule will
never be matched"); unguarded irrefutable arms make coverage total;
unguarded constructor/literal arms accumulate name and bool coverage.
After the walk, type-directed coverage closes the remaining cases: bool
scrutinees need true and false, option scrutinees need Some and None,
declared unions need every registered case. Anything still open is the
"Incomplete pattern matches" warning - a warning, not an error, exactly
as the F# compiler reports FS0025.
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_match_exhaustiveness" takes analyzer as Integer, scrutinee_type as Integer, match_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check one match expression for exhaustiveness and redundancy

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with match_node, 16
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with match_node, 24

    Let covered_names be proc list_create from List
    Let bool_flags be proc allocate from Layout with 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with bool_flags, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with bool_flags, 8, 0

    Let total_cover be 0
    Let reported_redundant be 0

    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let case_node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let case_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case_node, 16
        Let case_child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case_node, 24

        If case_child_count is greater than 0:
            If total_cover is equal to 1:
                If reported_redundant is equal to 0:
                    proc add_semantic_warning with analyzer, "This rule will never be matched"
                    Set reported_redundant to 1
                End If
            End If

            Let pattern_node be proc list_get from List with case_children, 0
            Let pattern_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 0

            Let guarded be 0
            Let effective_pattern be pattern_node
            If pattern_kind is equal to AST_PATTERN_GUARD from Parser:
                Set guarded to 1
                Let guard_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 16
                Let guard_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pattern_node, 24
                If guard_count is greater than 0:
                    Set effective_pattern to proc list_get from List with guard_children, 0
                End If
            End If

            If guarded is equal to 0:
                Let irrefutable be proc pattern_is_irrefutable with effective_pattern
                If irrefutable is equal to 1:
                    Set total_cover to 1
                End If
                proc collect_pattern_coverage with analyzer, effective_pattern, covered_names, bool_flags
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If total_cover is equal to 0:
        Let resolved be proc resolve_type with analyzer, scrutinee_type
        Let tag be proc type_tag with resolved

        If tag is equal to TYPE_BOOL:
            Let has_true be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bool_flags, 0
            Let has_false be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bool_flags, 8
            If has_true is equal to 1:
                If has_false is equal to 1:
                    Set total_cover to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If

        If tag is equal to TYPE_OPTION:
            Let has_some be proc name_list_contains with covered_names, "Some"
            Let has_none be proc name_list_contains with covered_names, "None"
            If has_some is equal to 1:
                If has_none is equal to 1:
                    Set total_cover to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If

        If tag is equal to TYPE_UNION:
            Let case_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with resolved, 16
            Let case_count be proc list_length from List with case_list
            Let all_present be 1
            Let c be 0
            While c is less than case_count:
                Let case_name be proc list_get from List with case_list, c
                Let present be proc name_list_contains with covered_names, case_name
                If present is equal to 0:
                    Set all_present to 0
                End If
                Set c to c plus 1
            End While
            If case_count is greater than 0:
                If all_present is equal to 1:
                    Set total_cover to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If total_cover is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_warning with analyzer, "Incomplete pattern matches on this expression"
    End If

    proc list_destroy from List with covered_names
    proc deallocate from Layout with bool_flags
    Return total_cover
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Module Passes
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
First pass over the program: registers modules, namespaces, and opens
into the module table and every type declaration into the type
environment, recursing through module/namespace nesting so forward
references during the declarations pass resolve. Runs before any
inference touches expressions.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_module_structure" takes analyzer as Integer, ast_root as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Register modules, opens, and type declarations

    If ast_root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 0

    Let is_container be 0
    If node_kind is equal to AST_PROGRAM from Parser:
        Set is_container to 1
    End If
    If node_kind is equal to AST_MODULE from Parser:
        Set is_container to 1
    End If
    If node_kind is equal to AST_NAMESPACE from Parser:
        Set is_container to 1
    End If

    If is_container is equal to 1:
        If node_kind is not equal to AST_PROGRAM from Parser:
            Let name_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 8
            Let module_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with name_token
            If module_name is not equal to 0:
                Let module_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 32
                proc hashtable_set from Dict with module_table, module_name, ast_root
            End If
        End If

        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 16
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 24
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let child be proc list_get from List with children, i
            proc analyze_module_structure with analyzer, child
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to AST_OPEN from Parser:
        Set name_token to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 8
        Let open_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with name_token
        If open_name is not equal to 0:
            Set module_table to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 32
            proc hashtable_set from Dict with module_table, open_name, ast_root
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to AST_TYPE_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc register_type_declaration with analyzer, ast_root
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Second pass: type-checks every declaration. Module-level let bindings
bind their names in the module symbol table (rec pre-binding included);
val declarations bind their declared signature; modules and namespaces
recurse; type declarations and opens were handled by the structure pass.
Any other shape is treated as an expression statement and inferred for
its diagnostics.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_module_declarations" takes analyzer as Integer, ast_root as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Type-check all declarations

    If ast_root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 0

    Let is_container be 0
    If node_kind is equal to AST_PROGRAM from Parser:
        Set is_container to 1
    End If
    If node_kind is equal to AST_MODULE from Parser:
        Set is_container to 1
    End If
    If node_kind is equal to AST_NAMESPACE from Parser:
        Set is_container to 1
    End If

    If is_container is equal to 1:
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 16
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 24
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let child be proc list_get from List with children, i
            proc analyze_module_declarations with analyzer, child
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to AST_LET_BINDING from Parser:
        proc analyze_let_binding_declaration with analyzer, ast_root
        Return 1
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to AST_VALUE_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Let name_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 8
        Let value_name be proc get_token_text from Lexer with name_token

        Let value_type be TYPE_ANY
        Set children to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 16
        Set child_count to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast_root, 24
        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let type_node be proc list_get from List with children, 0
            Set value_type to proc resolve_type_expr with analyzer, type_node
        End If

        proc define_symbol with analyzer, value_name, value_type
        Return 1
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to AST_TYPE_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If
    If node_kind is equal to AST_OPEN from Parser:
        Return 1
    End If

    proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, ast_root
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Drains the lazy parts of the substitution store: every bound slot is
fully resolved through its chain and written back (path compression), so
the late passes (exhaustiveness over resolved scrutinee types) and any
caller reading types afterwards see one-step resolutions. Occurs checks
already ran at bind time, so this pass cannot diverge.
@End Reasoning

Process called "solve_all_constraints" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compress all substitution chains to their final bindings

    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    Let subst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 0
    Let count be proc list_length from List with subst

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let bound be proc list_get from List with subst, i
        If bound is not equal to 0:
            Let final be proc resolve_type with analyzer, bound
            proc list_set from List with subst, i, final
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Late exhaustiveness pass: every registered match re-checks against its
scrutinee type AFTER all unifications have landed, so scrutinees that
were free variables at match-typing time are judged with their final
types (a match over a parameter later constrained to a declared union
gets real case coverage analysis).
@End Reasoning

Process called "validate_pattern_completeness" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Run exhaustiveness analysis over every registered match

    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    Let match_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 16
    Let count be proc list_length from List with match_registry

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let pair be proc list_get from List with match_registry, i
        Let match_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pair, 0
        Let scrutinee_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pair, 8
        proc validate_match_exhaustiveness with analyzer, scrutinee_type, match_node
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sweeps the definitions registry for local bindings (lambda parameters,
let-expression bindings, pattern variables) that were never looked up.
Underscore-prefixed names are the F# convention for intentionally-unused
binders and are exempt; module-level definitions are exported surface
and were never registered as local. One warning per unused name.
@End Reasoning

Process called "check_unused_definitions" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Warn about unused local bindings

    Let solver be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    Let definitions be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with solver, 24
    Let count be proc list_length from List with definitions

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let symbol be proc list_get from List with definitions, i

        Let is_local be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with symbol, 24
        Let is_used be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with symbol, 8

        If is_local is equal to 1:
            If is_used is equal to 0:
                Let symbol_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with symbol, 16
                If symbol_name is not equal to 0:
                    Let first_char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with symbol_name, 0
                    If first_char is not equal to 95:
                        If first_char is not equal to 0:
                            Let message be proc pool_concat with analyzer, "Unused binding: ", symbol_name
                            proc add_semantic_warning with analyzer, message
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Analysis Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level analysis sequence: clear prior results, register structure
(modules, opens, type declarations and their constructors), type-check
every declaration, compress the substitution store, judge match
exhaustiveness against final types, and sweep for unused locals. Null
AST is a hard error because the front end should never invoke analysis
on absent input.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_fsharp_module" takes analyzer as Integer, ast_root as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze a complete F# module

    If ast_root is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "No AST provided for analysis"
        Return 0
    End If

    proc clear_analysis_results with analyzer

    proc analyze_module_structure with analyzer, ast_root

    proc analyze_module_declarations with analyzer, ast_root

    proc solve_all_constraints with analyzer

    proc validate_pattern_completeness with analyzer

    proc check_unused_definitions with analyzer

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Public API
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public driver alias following the universal-translation "<lang>_analyze_
ast" naming convention. Returns 1 only when analysis ran and produced
zero errors; warnings do not fail the run.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_fsharp_ast" takes analyzer as Integer, ast_root as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Main entry point for F# semantic analysis

    Let analysis_result be proc analyze_fsharp_module with analyzer, ast_root

    Let error_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 40
    Let error_count be proc list_length from List with error_list

    If error_count is greater than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return analysis_result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Accessor returning the error list (offset 40). The driver walks this
list to surface diagnostics; ownership remains with the analyzer until
destroy_fsharp_semantic_analyzer runs.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_semantic_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get list of semantic errors

    Let error_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 40
    Return error_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Companion accessor for the warning list (offset 48) with the same
ownership contract as get_semantic_errors.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_semantic_warnings" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get list of semantic warnings

    Let warning_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    Return warning_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Predicate the driver gates code generation on: nonzero when any error
was recorded.
@End Reasoning

Process called "has_semantic_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if analyzer has semantic errors

    Let error_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 40
    Let error_count be proc list_length from List with error_list
    Return error_count
End Process
